title: hot pepper relish
directions: Cut peppers in half; slice halves in small strips.
Do not remove all of the seeds from the hot peppers.
Slice onions.
Put all ingredients into large container.
Bring to a boil.
If you need more liquid, add more vinegar and sugar.
Put into hot jars and seal as soon as mixture comes to a boil.
This is a good relish to put on sandwiches.

title: potato cheese hurry up(microwave)
directions: Mix soup, onions, dill weed and pepper in quiche dish.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 10 to 13 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Stir after 5 minutes.
Stir and sprinkle cheese on top before serving.

title: double fudge picnic cake
directions: Cook chocolate
pudding with milk. When it just starts to thicken, take off heat and beat in chocolate cake mix.
Spread quickly in buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, longer, if needed.

title: better than meat loaf
directions: Return to oven for 1/2 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Loaf will have a softer texture than most meat loaves.

title: mrs. creason's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add the sugar.
Cream together until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift flour before measuring and add to it the spices and the salt (the salt isn't necessary if you are using all butter).
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add it and the flour mixture alternately to the sugar-butter-egg mixture, beating after each addition.
Lightly dredge the nuts and fruit with a little extra flour and add.
Next add the jam.
Stir to get good distribution.
Grease and paper-line 2 (9-inch) cake pans, 2 inches deep.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.
Ice with a caramel icing of your choice.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill overnight or about 3 hours.
Top by layering the veggies.
Serve with taco chips.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix well. In a separate bowl, combine eggs, oil and strawberries. Mix well. Add strawberry mix to flour mix. Stir well and spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine with onion. Thaw broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Can add pimiento for color.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly; spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread crushed potato chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: portuguese eggs
directions: Alternate layers of bread cubes, cheese and sausage in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients with lightly beaten eggs.
Pour over the contents of dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tahitian salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except Jell-O.
After all ingredients are mixed well, sprinkle dry Jell-O over and fold in with other ingredients.
Then fold in mini marshmallows to your own desire.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Sift together sugar, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and flour. Add milk, egg and melted butter.
Spray flat square pan with Pam. Spread batter in pan; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 10 minutes in quick oven (400°).
Quick and easy.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking, without stirring, until syrup reaches 270° or forms a brittle ball when dropped in cold water. Add vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped corn.
Mix thoroughly to cover all kernels. Grease hands with butter and shape into balls.

title: spicy cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut X's in top of bread almost all the way through.
Wrap in foil 1/2 say up (do not cover top).
Fold cheese and stuff into X's.
Mix ingredients and pour into X's and spread over top.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, longer if needed.

title: grandma goldie's divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until a soft ball is formed in cold water.
Pour half of this mixture over beaten egg whites. Beat mixture with heavy spoon by hand.
You will need a towel as this mixture is hot.
Put rest of mixture back on stove and boil for awhile.
Pour that over other mixture, beating all the time by hand. Add vanilla and nuts. Beat until mixture comes together. Pour in buttered platter.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: bachelors delight
directions: Brown meat and pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Chop onions fine, including some of the green tops.
Blend onions with cream cheese and sour cream.
Grease a baking dish lightly.
Make layers of noodles, meat sauce, sour cream mixture and grated cheese, ending with grated cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker crust(for diabetic lemon pie)
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and press into a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Chill before filling.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Layer uncrushed graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of uncrushed graham crackers over pudding.
Then add rest of pudding on top.
Then add another layer of graham crackers.
Cover with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate or freeze for 24 hours.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: meatballs
directions: Put everything in slow cooker. Cook on high for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with pasta or on buns for meatball subs.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease mini muffin tins and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes or until golden.
Cook sausage and crumble; blot dry.
Combine with cheeses, olives, red pepper and salad dressing.
Fill wrappers with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.
Wrappers can be made a day ahead and I kept sausage mixture for a few days.

title: crab cakes helen
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, egg, celery salt and onion and continue cooking until very thick.
Remove spine from crab meat and add to mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Form into cakes or cut into steak shape pieces.
Dip each cake or steak into flour, then spread generously on both sides with mayonnaise and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in hot butter.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and boil raw sweet potatoes, then mash.
Add sugar, salt, spices, vanilla, lemon juice and melted butter.
Beat eggs slightly and add to other ingredients, then add milk and mix thoroughly.
Add additional spice seasoning to suit taste.
Bake in pie shells at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream filled brownies
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla and set aside. Melt chocolate and butter and cool. Beat sugar and eggs and add to chocolate mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add flour mixture to chocolate and mix well.
Pour 1/2 into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top, then spread remaining 1/2 of chocolate on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Top with chocolate frosting, if desired.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Beat egg in measuring cup; add vinegar and finish filling with water to measure 1 cup.
Mix with flour mixture.
Put in plastic bag; close securely.
Store in refrigerator.
This may be rolled to use immediately or will keep three to four weeks in refrigerator.
This is very easy to handle and can be rolled as much as necessary.
(Pastry for 6 or more one-crust pies.)

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain and combine the remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Heat thoroughly. Do not boil.
Festive on holidays.
Serves 6.

title: chewy cranberry cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Add apple juice concentrate, egg whites and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating at slow speed to form a soft dough.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts. Drop dough by level tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: praline graham crackers
directions: Combine butter, margarine and sugar.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes.
Lay crackers on cookie sheet.
Spread melted mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: chewy pecan cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: party punch
directions: Chill juices and ginger ale.
Make Kool-Aid using the ice water and 1 cup sugar.

title: joyce's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, vanilla and sugar.
Melt butter.
Add this to the mixture and add nuts. Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for 30-35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together; add pumpkin.
Stir well.
Add dry ingredients in this order and stir after adding each one: soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and flour.
After stirring well, add water and stir just until mixed.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans, 9 x 5-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean when inserted in middle.

title: hot cranapple punch
directions: Microwave in 2-quart covered micro-safe dish, juices, spices and sugar (leaving out orange slices and whole cloves) on high 9 or 10 minutes until boiling.
Strain into warmed punch bowl.
Use clove-studded orange slices as garnish.

title: apple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt, sugar and coconut.
Add hot milk while stirring.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Drain.
Spread in casserole dish and add cream of mushroom soup on top.
Add Tater Tots and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and Tots are cooked.

title: lasagna with zucchini
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as directed. Drain.

Brown sausage and rinse with water to remove excess fat. Mix eggs and Ricotta cheese. Spread 2 cups of spaghetti sauce over bottom of 11 x 16 x 2-inch lasagna pan. Top with layer of noodles. Layer zucchini slices over noodles and cover with 2 cups spaghetti sauce.
Place layer of noodles over sauce and top with Ricotta cheese mixture and half of Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.
Place a layer of noodles over Ricotta cheese.
Top with sausage and 2 cups of spaghetti sauce.
Top with remaining noodles and remaining Parmesan and Mozzarella cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt onto wax paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl at high speed until foamy white.
Slowly beat in 1/2 of the sugar until stiff.

title: snow peas oriental
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil and place over medium heat until hot.
Add snow peas and carrots.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir until cornstarch dissolves; add to vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickens.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salami
directions: Mix well and form into 2 loaves.
Wrap in heavy duty foil. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Place wrapped loaves in pan of cold water to cover.
Boil 1 hour.
Drain on paper towel.
Wrap and chill.
May be frozen.

title: ranch vegetables
directions: Combine dressing mix with 2 tablespoons oil in a large bowl. Mix with 32 ounces mixed frozen vegetables and toss.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes. Serves 8.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, oregano and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheeses; warm until melted.

title: bacon ala lisa
directions: Wrap water chestnuts in 1/3 to 1/2 strip of bacon; secure with toothpick.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan with toothpicks up.
Oven brown 1/2 hour; drain off fat.
Mix the brown sugar, chili sauce and mayo until blended.
Pour mixture over chestnuts.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: millionaire pie for diabetics
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until firm.
Delicious.

title: all american pie
directions: Put into saucepan sugar, cornstarch and lemonade.
Boil until thick.
Pour over fruit.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Put whipped cream on top.

title: 7-layer pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order shown.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: weight watchers pie
directions: Mix
together
milk
and pudding. Set aside to thicken. Heat peanut butter and honey in microwave for 30 seconds.
Mix with Rice
Krispies
and press into pie pan. (Use sandwich bag over hand;
makes this easier as the mixture is sticky.) Slice banana over
crust
and top with pudding. Chill until firm and top with Cool Whip.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler;
beat
with
electric
beater
for
1 minute to blend. Place
over
boiling water and cook, beating constantly, until frosting
forms stiff peaks, about 7 minutes.
Don't overcook! Remove
from boiling water.
Pour into mixing bowl; add vanilla. Beat
until
of
spreading
consistency, about 2 minutes. Frost top and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Mix together the corn meal, salt and pepper. Melt butter in large frying pan.
Dip tomato slices into mixture and fry until golden brown.

title: candyrok
directions: Stir all ingredients over low heat until dissolved. Cook without stirring over quick heat to the hard-crack stage of 310°. Remove from heat and add food coloring, any color. Pour into a greased cookie sheet or shallow pan. When cool, break into pieces.

title: mango fruit parfait
directions: Combine the mangoes and orange juice in a blender.
Puree until smooth.
Slice 20 strawberries. Set 4 remaining strawberries aside.
Line the bottoms of 4 balloon glasses with strawberry slices.
Pour a thin layer of mango puree over each to cover. Reserve 4 kiwi slices for garnish.
Divide remainder of kiwi slices into 4 portions.
Layer 1 portion on top of puree in each glass.
Pour remaining mango puree equally among the glasses. Top each parfait with a slice of kiwi.
Surround with raspberries. Place 1 strawberry on rim of each glass.
Cover parfaits with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: teriyaki steak appetizers
directions: Wipe steak with damp paper towels.
Trim off any excess fat. Cut steak in half lengthwise.
Slice across the grain in very thin slices, no more than 1/4-inch thick.
In small bowl, mix well rest of ingredients (except water chestnuts) for marinade.
Wrap each chestnut in a steak slice and fasten with wooden pick.
Dip in marinade.
Arrange in shallow glass pan.
Pour rest of marinade over the steak-wrapped chestnuts, coating well.
Let stand covered in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Turn after 1 hour to marinate other side.
Place on ungreased rack in broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat, about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook.
Arrange on warm platter.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: Melt butter and smear butter on sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread garlic evenly on bottom only.
Lay potato slices flat on bottom of pan.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over potato slices.
Mix grated cheeses together and sprinkle evenly over potatoes.
Sprinkle some paprika over top.
Cover with foil or casserole lid and bake for 50 minutes at 425°.
Uncover and brown tops of potatoes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Finely chop crabmeat and onion together in a bowl. Let cream cheese sit out for a bit to soften and then slowly add to crab and onion mixture. Put in milk and horseradish and mix all together until pasty. Add salt and pepper to taste (optional). Transfer to an oven-safe (medium size) bowl and sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes. Bread crumbs should brown and mixture should bubble.

title: libby's corned beef spaghetti(for a family meal)
directions: Saute vegetables with oregano in a very little fat or oil. Add tomato sauce and seasoning to taste.
Pour over a platter full of spaghetti cooked to your taste and sprinkle with sharp, finely grated cheese (queso de bola or Parmesan).
Pass extra sauce and cheese at the table.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix together until spreading consistency.
Serve with party rye.
Sprinkle dill weed on top.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Drain peaches well; set aside on plate lined with paper towels.
Combine baking mix, 3/4 cup brown sugar, buttermilk, eggs, oil, orange peel and baking soda with mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared skillet.
Spread evenly.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add hamburger and stir until redness is gone.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 to 2 hours at 325° or in crock-pot.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add margarine.
Drop by tablespoons into skillet and fry like potato cakes, browning both sides.

title: rice fluff pudding
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and bake, uncovered, with 3 to 4 hour dinner.
Serve over sliced oranges.
Raisins and cinnamon may be used instead of orange rind, if desired.

title: texas gold bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oleo well.
Put in a jellyroll pan, 12 x 15-inches.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pat into first layer.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread over first layer. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together with low speed of mixer the beaten egg yolks. Add and mix well the flour, soda and buttermilk.
Sift flour and soda together. Add alternating, the vanilla, coconut and pecans. Add and mix the 5 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Fold in.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350°.

title: the fudge lady's fudge
directions: Spray an 11 x 17-inch pan with butter-flavored Pam and set aside.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Add vinegar, then vanilla.
Beat until stiff! Fold in chocolate chips and pecans with wire whisk.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunday afternoon delight
directions: With a fork, cream margarine, flour and nuts together until it is crumbly.
Spread mixture evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake crust at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Let crust cool completely before filling.

title: indian meal pudding
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Place dish in pan of water and bake in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Stir pudding while cooking (approximately every 15 minutes).

title: dressing for chicken or turkey
directions: Mix and add enough sweet milk for right consistency.
Bake in greased skillet.
Break up while hot and mix with liquid from hen or turkey.
Put back in pan and brown.

title: jello and cream cheese
directions: Make jello according to directions on box.
However, use only 2 cups of water.
Stir until dissolved.
Use mixer and mix in cream cheese.
Add pineapple and Cheddar cheese.
Stir and pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on muffin halves.
Cut each muffin into 6 triangles.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. After frozen store in a plastic bag in the freezer until ready to use.
Bake and serve hot.
350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 72 bite size pieces.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion until tender.
Remove from skillet; add meat and saute until it changes color.
Add vegetables and mushroom soup along with onion.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Crumble up toasted bread and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Then sprinkle cheese on top and let melt.

title: stir and drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork.
Stir in Wesson oil, vanilla and lemon peel.
Blend in sugar.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Stamp each cookie flat with bottom of glass that has been dipped in reserved mixture, then in additional sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once from cookie sheet.
If cookies are baked one cookie sheet at a time, stir dough between each batch. Yields 60 cookies.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time; add remaining ingredients.
Place in cold oven set at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn up to 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool on wire rack for 20 minutes.
Turn over and remove from pan.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Heat mushroom soup and stir in grated cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Combine soup mixture with the remaining ingredients (except butter and crackers).
Add salt to taste.
Pour mixture in greased casserole dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top and sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry sauce mix
directions: In 1-quart jar, combine first 5 ingredients.
Add soy sauce and vinegar.
Shake until blended.
Add broth, sherry and water. Shake well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator up to 2 weeks; shake before using.
Can be frozen in 1 cup portions (thaw and shake well).
Makes 4 cups.

title: green gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins in water in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Mix gently until well blended. Pour into mold or 13 x 9 pan. Chill until firm. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: lite pear salad(serves 12)
directions: Drain pears. Reserve 1 cup syrup; if needed, add water to equal 1 cup. Over medium-high heat, combine syrup and jello. Bring to a boil and stir until dissolves. Remove from heat. Chill until partially set. In large bowl, blend cream cheese and pears until smooth. Add gelatin mixture and Cool Whip. Blend until smooth. Pour in mold or leave in bowl. Chill 3 hours or until firm. Weight Watchers points: 2 per serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and simmer with spaghetti sauce, onion and oregano for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles until soft.
In a greased casserole dish, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat the layers.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Place drained shrimp in long, glass bowl.
Sprinkle with celery seed.
Place onion slices and bay
leaves
on top.
Mix other ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 7 days before serving.
When ready to serve, remove shrimp from marinade and serve in bowl set in ice.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge(low carb)
directions: Melt the cream cheese and peanut butter in microwave for 2 minutes, stopping and stirring at 1 minute intervals. Melt chocolate in separate bowls until creamy. Combine chocolate with cream cheese mixture and whisk in sweetener and cream. Pour into (Pam'd) glass pan or pan lined with aluminum foil. Chill at least 4 hours. Cut in squares and enjoy. Fudge will be gooey. For a more solid fudge, put in freezer 30 minutes before cutting.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo, oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift remaining ingredients together and gradually add to liquid mixture, blending well.
Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets and flatten with the bottom of a small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: reese's pie
directions: Cook pie shell.
Cool.
Put cooked vanilla pudding mixed with peanut butter in bottom of shell.
Let cool to firm.
Fill with chocolate pudding. Cool.
Top with cream. Serve cold.

title: drizzle icing for angel food cake or thumbprint cookies
directions: May tint with few drops of food coloring according to the holiday or occasion.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix soup, dressing and preserves together; put on top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can serve with rice.

title: potato salad for large crowd(30 people or more)
directions: Cook potatoes; cool, peel and chop.
Add eggs, bell peppers, onions, pimento, celery and pickles.
Make sauce by mixing well the pickle juice, mustard and 3 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Add about 1 quart mayonnaise, salt and pepper to the sauce.
When potato mixture is cold, add sauce all at one time to mixture.

title: kraut salad
directions: Cut up kraut.
Combine with celery, onion, carrot and peppers. Dissolve sugar in oil and vinegar.
Add celery seed.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Cover; chill for several hours.
Drain before serving (optional).
Makes 8 servings.
Good with seafood and vegetables.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and place in a 9 x 11-inch greased baking dish. Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg.
Sprinkle this mixture over the diced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Pour 1/2 cup of melted butter over the top of mixture.
Bake for about 40 minutes or until brown.
Also good made with peaches, berries, etc.
Serve warm with whipped cream topping.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all together except chocolate chips. Stir until smooth. Add chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In a greased casserole dish, mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle more cheese on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water. Work shortening into flour; add buttermilk and yeast.
Stir well; roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potatoes in large baking dish and put green beans on top.
Sprinkle celery and onion on top of green beans.
Mix 2/3 cup cream of mushroom soup with milk and pour over green beans. Place pork chops on top and dot with remaining mushroom soup. Cover with foil and bake until pork chops are tender at 350°.

title: edible napkin rings
directions: Spray vegetable spray on outside of an ovenproof pudding dish that is not over 2-inch circumference at base.
Wrap breadstick around base and tie a knot.
Bake according to bread package instructions.
Cool.
Remove dish.
Slip a napkin through opening, and eat ring with your meal.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Pour oil into 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Scrub potatoes and cut into wedges lengthwise. Blot wedges with paper towel and place in pan. Turn to coat evenly with the oil, leaving potato cut side up in a single layer. Sprinkle with paprika, salt, pepper and cheese, if used. Adjust seasonings. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until fork-tender. Serve plain or with sour cream. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bachelor chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breast with meat mallet. Place on square of aluminum foil. Top with broccoli. Add salt and pepper, 1 tablespoon margarine and 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Fold foil over and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Brown 1 pound sausage and onion; drain. Crumble or tear 6 slices dry bread and add to sausage. Mix 4 eggs (slightly beaten), salt, pepper and 2 cups milk together. Combine with sausage and bread mixture; add 1 teaspoon curry powder. Let mixture set in bowl overnight in refrigerator.
Pour mixture into greased Pyrex dish (11 x 7-inches). Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes, covered with foil. Remove foil and let brown a little.

title: quick nut fudge(no cook)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Spread in large, square pan lined with wax paper.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: frozen hawaiian pie
directions: In a bowl, combine milk and whipped topping. Gently fold in pineapple, nuts, cherries and lemon juice. Pour into the crusts. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Remove from the freezer 20 minutes before serving. Garnish with mint, nuts and cherries. Yield: 2 pies, 6 to 8 servings each.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Brown beef then add taco seasoning (do not add water).
Mix cornbread to package directions.
Add can of creamed corn, eggs and salt and mix well.
Spray an iron skillet with Pam.
Add 1/2 cornbread mix to skillet; add beef, onion, green chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread mix over top and smooth out. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flours, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; stir just until moistened (batter may be lumpy).
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups two-thirds full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until top of muffin springs back when lightly touched.
Yields 18 to 22 muffins.
These are delicious!

title: coconut pie(no crust)
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend together flour and sugar.
Stir into eggs. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch pie plates.
(Do not use crusts.)
Bake at 300° for about 30 to 40 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: sausage zucchini dish
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, onion, water and oregano.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender in a small amount of boiling salted water; drain.
Season with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Stir in chicken soup, sour cream and pimiento.
Combine 1/2 cup margarine and stuffing mix, stirring until well blended.

title: crab rangoon(appetizers)
directions: Mix crab, spices and cream cheese.
Put spoonful in each wonton wrapper and pinch to close.
Fry in deep oil in deep fryer on high until golden brown.
Remove and drain on paper towels. Great for snacks or to accompany Chinese food!

title: pineapple mint coolers
directions: Mix in 1/2 gallon pitcher; add to top with water (for concentrated lemonade).
Pour over ice cubes or mix in blender with ice to make icee.
Garnish with sprig of fresh mint.
Great summer refresher.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and buttermilk, alternating to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with buttermilk.
Mix until moist.
Stir in lemon juice and rind and pecans.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 20 minutes; cool.
Add other ingredients to cooled mixture and mix well.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Dribble powdered sugar icing on cooled bars.

title: quick kahlua fudge sauce
directions: In heavy 1-quart saucepan, combine ingredients and mix well. Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Reheat before serving.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onions in margarine.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Add sauteed onions.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat; bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: little king salad
directions: Just before serving time, toss with the following:

title: ice tea
directions: You will also need a 10-cup coffee maker and 1 gallon glass container.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Place rice in a greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Cover with combined vegetables and seasonings.
Combine soup and Miracle Whip salad dressing; mix well.
Gradually add water to soup mix, mixing until blended.
Pour 1/2 of soup mix over vegetables.
Top with chicken and remaining soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine sugar and cocoa in a large microwave safe bowl.
Make a well in mixture and in it put butter, milk and vanilla.
Do not mix!
Cook on High power for 3 minutes.
Mix immediately.
Add nuts. Pour into a buttered 9-inch pie plate or square dish and let stand until set firm.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and beat until smooth. Add cereal. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chili
directions: In a heavy saucepan cook meat, onion and peppers until meat is lightly browned and veggies are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce, beans, salt, chili powder and bay leaf.
Cook on low for at least 6 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Makes 1 pint.

title: chocolate coconut drops
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat or double boiler. Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, coconut and walnuts.
Drop mixture by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Place in a 350° oven. Turn off heat and leave in oven about 15 minutes until it has glazed appearance.
Remove from pan while warm.

title: frito dip
directions: Brown sausage; add onions.
Cook until tender.
While the sausage is cooking, put cheese and tomatoes (break tomatoes into little pieces) into a removable crock-pot.
Put in the microwave and melt.
Drain off fat on sausage and add to cheese mixture. Keep hot in crock-pot.
Serve with Fritos.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together in food processor.
Pour in graham cracker crust.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place meat in a microwave safe dish.
Add cream of chicken soup and enough milk to make creamy. Place tater tots over entire meat mixture.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes in microwave on high.

title: no cholesterol pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Mix margarine, sugar, Egg Beaters and flavoring in large bowl.
Mix 1 minute on low speed, then 5 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl several times.
Mix flour and baking powder together.

While beating at low speed, mix flour and milk alternately into sugar mixture, scraping sides of bowl frequently. Pour in pan and bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes (check with straw for doneness after 1 hour).
Cool in pan 25 minutes; remove to plate.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles according to directions; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Place half noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the Mozzarella cheese and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Makes 12 servings.
Can be assembled and refrigerated early.
Allow an extra 15 minutes in oven.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Garnish with extra cheese.

title: pink fluff salad
directions: Mix the pudding directly from the envelope with the cool whip.
Empty pineapple w/juice into the cherry pie filling. Combine the cool whip with the pie filling and chill.

title: mandarin and marmalade cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend butter and sugar with an electric mixer to form a grainy paste.
Add egg and orange marmalade and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add the flour mixture and the oranges and blend at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 24 to 25 minutes or until the bottoms of cookies begin to brown.
Transfer with a spatula to a cool, flat surface.

title: no bake cheese torte
directions: Beat cheese with sugar and fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour in crust lined pan and sprinkle with 3/4 cup crumb mixture.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise, onions, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli. Pour into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour melted butter over cheese.
Spread cracker crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Blend honey, peanut butter and powdered sugar until smooth. Roll into small balls and roll in crushed corn flakes. Refrigerate one hour or until cold.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Place in dish and refrigerate until congealed.
Makes large dish.

title: macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Stir in almonds; mix well. Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Garnish with your favorite candied fruit.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove immediately.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine
dressings; mix well and add other ingredients. Add more
Miracle
Whip if necessary.
Serve with tomatoes cut in wedges.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In casserole dish, pour rice, then water.
Mix remaining ingredients together and place on top of rice and water.
Check casserole during cooking; you might have to add some more water.
Cook at 350° until rice is done.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Put in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: chilli cheese soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add onion, green onions and garlic.
Cook until translucent.
Add tomatoes and green chilies, 1 cup water and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, then stir in the molasses. Then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate dough 1 hour.
Shape into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass base into circles.
They crack on top when baked.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: mama's coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and coconut in heavy saucepan.
Add milk, stirring over heat, then add eggs, butter and vanilla while stirring over medium heat.
Pudding done when mixture bubbles and becomes thickened.
Remove from heat.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, eggs, sugar and almond extract together. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool for 20 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour in a greased,
floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool cake 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and remaining ingredients, making a stiff dough.
Place in covered container in refrigerator.
Pinch off dough as needed.
Shape into biscuits. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake as many as you like.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: 3 in 1 cheese ball
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce until fluffy; divide in thirds.

title: irish potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skin; peel off skin while slightly warm. Drizzle vinegar combined with spices and sugar over warm potatoes. Set aside.
Combine mayo and milk; set aside.
Chop cabbage and dill pickles.
Cube meat.
Combine all but mayo and milk.
Mix well; then pour mayo and milk over everything.
Mix slightly. Chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Cook corn meal in water 10 minutes; add salt, sugar and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm, stirring occasionally to prevent a film.
When cool, add softened yeast and beat well.
Add flour and mix well.
Knead, using as little flour as possible.
Put into a greased bowl and let rise until almost doubled in bulk.
Knead down and let rise again.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large heavy saucepan and mix well. Cook, stirring occasionally, over low to medium heat, until the sauce has reduced by half and is quite thick, about one hour. Remove from heat and cool, covered tightly and refrigerate.
May be stored up to 4 weeks.
Delicious over chicken, grilled pork chops and spareribs.
Best made one day in advance before using.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: more
directions: Brown meat, add onion, pepper, celery, garlic, chili powder, tomato paste, tomatoes, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 1 hour, covered.
Add corn and peas; cook 15 minutes more.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
In oblong pan, spread 1/2 spaghetti, 1/2 meat, 1/2 cheese; repeat.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spritz butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour and salt.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks and vanilla or almond extract.
Dough should form a ball.
Clean off sides of bowl.
Add a little more flour if too soft.
Refrigerate about 5 minutes. Press out cookies from press onto ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate with chips, sprinkles, nuts, etc.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, combine soup mix
and 1/2 cup water; beat in eggs with fork.
Add beef; mix well.
Shape mixture into meatballs.
Combine sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, chili sauce, 3/4 cup water and the brown sugar.
Pour half of the mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set remaining mixture aside.
In skillet, brown meatballs quickly.
Drain.
Arrange atop of sauerkraut in pan.
Pour remaining mixture over meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serve
over rice.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and put over heat. Meanwhile, put 1/3 cup of sugar on to melt, then pour into first mixture, which has boiled, and add Karo.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add butter, cool and beat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and add milk.
Warm to 105° to 115°.
Stir in sugar, salt and yeast until dissolved.
Place flour in large bowl.
Make well in flour and pour in liquid.
Stir until blended. Cover.
Let rise until doubled, 1 hour or longer.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Drain juice from defrosted raspberries, adding water to make 1/2 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add raspberry liquid and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream, marshmallows and raspberries.
Press crumbs in bottom of 6 x 10 x 1 3/4-inch pan. Pour raspberry mixture over crumbs and chill until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: two minute microwave velvet fudge
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Microwave chocolate chips and sweetened condensed milk, uncovered, in a 2-quart bowl on High for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth. Stir in powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan. Spread evenly. Chill until firm, about 1 1/2 hours. Cut into squares.

title: wheat thin candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Spread peanut butter mixture on Wheat Thins.
When all are finished, dip in melted dipping chocolate.
Place on wax paper to dry.

title: sunshine punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine all ingredients, except sherbet. Stir until juices are thawed and blended. Top with scoops of sherbet. Makes 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Pinch together on sides.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix mayonnaise, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and cream cheese.
Spread on crescent rolls.
Add vegetables, cheese and tomato last.

title: ham and spinach quiche
directions: Get pie shell. Layer each ingredient in the order as it is written. Get a medium bowl. Beat eggs, milk and add a little salt and pepper to season. Pour mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle sharp Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until edge of pie crust is brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook together raisins and water until about 5 tablespoons liquid remains; drain.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the cooled liquid and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in rolled oats and the cooked raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Prepare chicken.
Line flour tortilla with 1 slice of cheese and chicken; roll.
Place in lightly greased 12 x 9-inch dish. Mix soup concentrate, sour cream and pepper.
Pour over prepared tortillas. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
May add any vegetables desired.

title: holiday sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter 2 baking sheets.
Beat the butter and sugar in a large bowl until light and creamy.
In a separate bowl combine the eggs, milk, vanilla and lemon rind. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add the egg-milk mixture to the creamed butter, alternating with the sifted dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Divide the dough into 4 pieces and put each on a large piece of wax paper or aluminum foil.
Shape the dough into cylinders about 2 inches thick.
Wrap each cylinder well and chill for 2 hours or until very firm.
Cut the dough cylinders into slices about 1/4-inch thick and put them on the baking sheets about 1 inch apart.
Bake for 10 minutes until the cookies are very lightly browned. Sprinkle the cookies with superfine sugar and cool on wire racks. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: beef casserole
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal in a bowl and mix.
Place some cereal and sugar into a plastic bag and shake.
Keep adding more cereal and sugar until all is coated.

title: reese's pieces
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together and press in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on the top. Cut into squares.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove 12 outer leaves from cabbage and place leaves in a large Dutch oven.
Add boiling water to cover; let stand 30 to 50 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Heat soup, milk and cheese together until cheese is slightly melted. Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish. Bake in 325° to 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: In large kettle, cook and stir onion, carrot and garlic in oil until onion is tender.
Add fish fillets, lobster, tomatoes (with liquid), bay leaves and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, clams (with liquor) and remaining ingredients; simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Makes 12 servings.

title: eggnog thumbprints
directions: In a large mixer bowl beat 3/4 Cup butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar and brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla, and salt and beat well.
Add flour and beat until well mixed.
cover and chill about 1 hour or until easy to handle. Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down centers with thumb.
Bake in oven at 350 for about 12 minutes or until done.
Remove and cool.

title: jellied veal
directions: Cook until tender with green pepper, onion and salt.
Put through grinder with a little raw onion.
Strain stock and cook down until it makes 2 cups.
Pour over meat and chill.

title: warm salad of chicken, beans, rice and corn
directions: Combine rice with water and boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 17 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender. Grill or broil chicken 10 minutes.
In bowl, beat olive oil, lime juice and vinegar.
Beat in cumin.
Stir in scallions, jalapeno and garlic.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and add with beans to dressing.
About 5 minutes before rice is done, stir in corn to heat and stir rice mixture into dressing.
If using avocado, cut up and add and stir.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, lemon rind and juice, cornstarch, egg yolks and water and cook until thick. Pour into baked pie crusts.
Beat egg whites and sugar to taste and vanilla.
Cover pie and brown in oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmons, sugar and eggs together first.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together; add alternating with milk.
Mix in the butter last.
This rises high and falls when cool.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mashed banana.
Mix until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in paper lined muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: holiday date nut squares
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients 5 minutes; add margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Mix dry ingredients (Sweet 'N Low is optional) and add nuts.
Mix fruit mixture and dry ingredients and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
This is a cookie that most diabetics can eat.

title: crayfish and artichoke
directions: Place artichokes on bottom of greased casserole.
Mix all other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over artichokes.
Add cheese to top. Bake at 325° until brown.
May use shrimp or crabmeat in place of crayfish.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt, then add water. Cook until thick and clear. Cool slightly. Beat egg whites until frothy. Continue beating while slowly pouring cooked mixture over, then beat 5 minutes (no less). Cover cooled filling in pie shell with meringue. Seal edges to crust. Bake at 450° for 7 minutes, until golden brown.

title: giant-chocolate cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir in oats, cereal, coconut and chocolate chips.
Press 1 scant cup dough into 6-inch circle on foil lined cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining dough,
placing cookies 2 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 16 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry christmas candles
directions: Preparation:
30 minutes.
Heat cranberry sauce; strain.
Set berries aside.
Dissolve gelatin in hot juice and water.
Add salt and lemon juice.
Chill until thickened enough to mound slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Beat in real mayonnaise with rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Fold in cranberries, fruit and nuts.
Divide mixture evenly into eight 6 ounce fruit juice cans. Chill 4 hours or longer; unmold.
Garnish with salad greens.

title: angel cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend in brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Cover cookie sheet with parchment paper.
Drop cookie mix by spoonfuls onto parchment paper, spacing slightly to allow for spreading.

title: chocolate mice
directions: Drain cherries well; carefully pat dry without removing stems.
Put chocolate chips in microwaveable bowl and melt chips according to package instructions.
Set up a work area with cherries, melted chips, unwrapped Hershey Kisses, and almonds. Dip cherry into chocolate, covering cherry completely.
Quickly stick the flat end of the Hershey Kiss onto the chocolate covered cherry.
Place two almond slices between the Hershey Kiss and the cherry to make the ears.
Use the decorating gel to make eyes and nose on the Hershey Kiss.

title: broccoli "n" cheese puff
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Cook frozen broccoli in boiling salted water according to package directions. Drain well.
Line pan with bread sliced into triangles.
Combine broccoli with margarine, Swiss cheese slivers, dash of Tabasco and minced onion.
Spoon over bread.

title: spiced coconut-carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into muffin cups.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl mix buttermilk, egg and melted butter.
Pour in liquid ingredients over dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into greased cup.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: raw mushroom salad
directions: Toss mushrooms with lemon juice until slightly moistened.
Add onions, oil, salt and toss again.
Chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla. Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form. Add cream to peanut butter mixture and blend. Spoon into crust and place in freezer until set (30 to 40 minutes).
Heat chocolate and coffee in microwave and spread on top of pie.
Return to freezer, uncovered, until set (15 minutes).

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add to your freezer.
Be sure beaters and freezer are very cold.
Use layers of ice, salt and 1 cup water.
I use a whole box of table salt.
After freezer stops, let stand for 30 minutes before serving.
Very good!

title: snowballs
directions: Heat lard in deep fryer (I use shortening). Drop from teaspoon. Fry slowly in hot lard.

title: baked ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Place 6 slices in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with cheese slices and brush with mustard.
Cover with ground ham.
Butter remaining bread and place buttered side up on top of ham.
Mix eggs with milk and salt and pour over sandwiches. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Mix soup and broth and heat.
Serve as sauce. Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage patch
directions: Cut the cabbage and set aside.
Brown onion and hamburger; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cabbage; simmer until cabbage is done.
Serve with cornbread.

title: my favorite reuben(sandwich)
directions: Arrange meat on bread; top with dressing.
Add sauerkraut and heat in conventional oven, toaster oven or microwave oven (length of time will depend upon oven).
Remove from oven; top each slice with cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese is melted and bubbly. Yield: 4 open face sandwiches.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces. In large bowl, beat shortening and peanut butter until well blended.
Add 1/3 cup sugar and brown sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to peanut butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° about 3 minutes.

title: white bean soup
directions: Set aside last 3 ingredients.
Bring first 7 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
If it becomes too thick, add more broth.
When beans are tender, add the remaining 5 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 more minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add chopped onion and simmer until golden. Remove from heat.
Crush one sleeve of Ritz crackers until you achieve coarse crumbs. Stir cracker crumbs in butter/onion mixture. Add in can of clams. Stir until well mixed and spoon into an oven-safe bowl.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with remaining Ritz crackers.

title: my apple pie
directions: Mix apples with flour, sugar and spices and stir.
Heat water to just warm and add cornstarch and butter; pour over apples. Stir and put in 9-inch pie shell.
(Use second pie shell for top of pie crust.)
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: fiesta vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Chill 1 hour. Serve with assorted vegetables, crackers or chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: thai fried noodles
directions: Cook noodles as instructed on package and drain.
In a saucepan, cook meat in oil until almost done.
Stir in the onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Add Accent, salt, pepper, sugar and fish oil.
Add water a
little at a time.
Stir in the cooked noodles and soy sauce.
Serve while hot.

title: momo and justin's famous hot sauce
directions: Combine Ro-Tel and tomatoes in a large bowl.
In a blender, add remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup of tomato mixture.
Puree. Add to remaining tomato mixture.
Salt to taste.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.
Refrigerate.

title: savory cheese balls
directions: Grate the Cheddar cheese.
Set aside to warm to room temperature.
At the same time, have your cream cheese warming to room temperature.
When the cream cheese is very pliable, combine with the Cheddar, Worcestershire sauce and the chopped onion. Form into a ball.
Refrigerate until rather solid.
Roll in fine nuts; dot with sliced, stuffed olives.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: three-cheese shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions. Drain and rinse in cold water. In a bowl, combine next 10 ingredients. Divide the small jar of sauce between two ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking dishes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add Karo or honey and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Add to first mixture; add nuts.
Grease two 8-inch square pans.
Turn batter into pans and spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for 32 minutes. Don't overbake.
Cut into squares.
You can sprinkle with powdered sugar if you prefer.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and topping.
Spread over gelatin. Sprinkle with nuts or cookie crumbs.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir into sugar mixture the peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High until light.
Add margarine and vanilla to mixture, blending well.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Peanuts will be lightly brown and syrup hot. Add to mixture the soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto lightly buttered cookie pan.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzel sticks, sugar and butter together.
Set aside 4 tablespoons for garnish.
Press remainder into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Blend milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Press plastic wrap onto filling in saucepan and cool to room temperature.
Peel and slice bananas.
Arrange layer of banana slices 1/2-inch deep in pie shell.
Pour in cooled filling.
Chill for 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Cook beans in water.
Season with salt and bacon drippings, ham or other seasoning meat.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add onion, garlic, celery and bay leaf.
Continue to cook over low heat for 1/2 to 1 hour.
If beans become too dry, add heated water.
Two tablespoons of sugar improve the whole effect.
Serve on mounds of rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried fish (blue)
directions: Filet fish; remove skin and cut fish in small strips.
Mix the batter of all ingredients and let fish marinate for better flavor. Cook fish in 1/2-inch of cooking oil at 350° until done.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: For filling, mix hamburger, sausage, onion, potato, rice and kraut all together.
Set aside.
Put head of cabbage in boiling water until the leaves are wilted.
Separate the leaves.
Put the filling in the leaves, rolling up.
Pin together with toothpicks. Put rolls in large pot.
Pour tomato-juice over them.
Let set overnight.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pork tenderloin filets
directions: Cut pork tenderloins into pieces 2 1/2 to 3-inches long.
Take 2 to 3 pieces; turn on end and wrap with bacon (like filet mignon).
Use a very hot fire to sear.
Season with lemon pepper seasoning and garlic powder.
Ten minutes before pork is done, mix together Dijon mustard and cream to desired consistency, heating on stove over low heat.
Spoon over filets when serving.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add water to make approximately 6 quarts.
Freeze until slushy.
Place in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: mom's jiffy feather cake
directions: Do not beat or mix until all ingredients are together.
Begin by breaking egg into mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost with Minute Fudge Frosting.
Double for a large cake.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup onion in skillet.
Stir in catsup, chili powder and salt.
Mash in beans.
Heat through.
Garnish with the cheese, olives and 1/4 cup onion.
Serve hot with corn chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick.
Before removing from heat add.

title: pineapple gelatin salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Chill until thickened.
Stir in pineapple and coconut.
Chill.

title: white chili
directions: Use a large pot.
Chicken broth, beans on low heat.
Saute onions and garlic in tablespoon olive oil until tender.
Add green chilies with liquid.
Put in with broth and beans.
Add cubed chicken.

title: lemonade
directions: Peel and slice lemons. Put in jar, add sugar and water. Mix well. Let sit overnight.

title: paprika cheese potatoes
directions: Combine salt, milk, margarine (melted) and Parmesan cheese. Stir well.
In a medium pan or casserole dish, layer potatoes to about 3/4 full.
One layer of potatoes; add 1/2 of all cheeses, layer the rest of potatoes with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 350° oven until potatoes are completely done.
Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and Pet milk in blender.
Then pour into small pan and cook (stirring) until thick.
Add 1 tablespoon butter; stir.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.

title: oven scrambled eggs
directions: Place butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place in warm oven to melt.
Combine eggs, milk, seasonings and cheese.
Add mushrooms and ham; pour into baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven, stir well.
Return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until set. Cut into squares.
Serve.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add flour, potato chips and vanilla; beat well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes on cookie sheet; remove to wire racks.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place all ingredients, except macaroni, in a large pot.
Add water; pot should be about 3/4 full.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic, nutmeg and basil to taste.
Bring to boil, then simmer until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni; continue on simmer until macaroni is cooked to your liking.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs and whip whites.
Add in 4 1/2 tablespoons sugar.
Place in refrigerator.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Add egg yolks 2 at a time.
Add sifted flour and milk alternately.
On low speed, blend in egg whites.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325°
until done.

title: bird balls
directions: Cook 2 cups oats in 2-inches of water.
Remove from heat; add lard and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Cool and shape into balls.
Place into mesh bags.
Hang the bag on your bird feeder or a tree branch.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, omitting oil and adding 6 Tbsp. coconut.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 28 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cook in pan 10 minutes on a wire rack.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy 2 1/2-quart kettle or large skillet. Add onion and garlic; saute until pale golden.
Stir in beef and cook, stirring, until browned.
Add remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Mix well; cover and simmer over low heat for about 1 hour or until sauce is thickened and flavors are blended.
Cook the lasagna noodles in plenty of boiling salted water until just tender.
Drain thoroughly; dry well on paper towels.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and deep fry until brown.

title: pork chops parmesan
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Dredge chops in flour in plastic bag.
Melt margarine in large skillet; brown chops.
Lay chops overlapping in shallow 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon drippings over chops; cover with soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for mandarin oranges. Add them after everything else is mixed.
Refrigerate overnight. Serves 8 to 10.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil boston butt in pot until done.
Remove and debone, removing all fat and disposing of.
Chop up lean pork and set aside.
Also boil chicken in a pot.
Debone, removing and disposing of fat and skin.
Cut up lean chicken and put in with pork.
If using frozen corn, cook in microwave until about done. Grind up pork, chicken, corn, tomatoes and onion.
Mix all ingredients in a large, heavy- bottom pot. Cook on low heat about 1-1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Do not let stick to pot. Enough stew to serve 25 people.
Amount of all
ingredients can be adjusted for personal taste.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix the cake, using water and eggs as specified on the box. Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, mix butter, flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine; add brown sugar and let cool.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add balance of ingredients.
Pour into greased jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares when completely cool.

title: broccoli-slaw salad
directions: Mix everything together in order. Toss in packets from Ramen noodle soup. Chill.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/4 cups cold water. Add pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Put in tray and cover with miniature marshmallows and let jell.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix cheese, hash browns and sour cream. Melt margarine and pour over corn flakes in a pan, 9 x 13. Top with mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: no sugar fruit cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter and stir in pineapple juice, orange rind, vanilla and egg.
Add fruits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon, 2-inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together, put into a greased bowl and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Put ketchup on top before baking.

title: country cheese snacks
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Broil until golden & bubbly.
Garnish with olives and parsley.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift flour, cocoa and salt together and mix buttermilk with food coloring. Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid ingredients to creamed mixture. Beat well. Dissolve baking soda in vinegar and fold into batter. Grease and flour two 9-inch layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from the pans; cool and spread with Vanilla Filling and Frosting.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix butter, cream cheese and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time. Add flour, salt and vanilla and mix well. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green chili pie
directions: Line pie plate with split green chilies.
Mix eggs and milk and spoon over chilies.
Top with cheese.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: chili ham cups
directions: Spray muffin tin with Pam cooking spray.
Flatten biscuits in hand and place them in tins.
Soften cream cheese in microwave. Add chilies, ham, Cheddar cheese and chopped black olives.
Mix. Blend evenly in biscuits.
Bake at 370° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 10.

title: company tuna bake
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Don't choose too young and take only such as have been reared in good moral atmosphere.

Do not go to market for him as the best are always brought to your door. When once decided upon and selected, let that part remain forever settled and give your entire thought to the preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles, flavored with kisses to taste.
Then wrap them in a mantle of charity; keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands until well blended. Make dough into about 3 balls and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Use cookie press to make desired shape; bake in a 375° oven until slightly browned.
Do not overbake!

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix corn, milk, oil and eggs; add dry ingredients.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 batter.
Spread half of the peppers and cheese, then repeat process.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
(Where marked, I increase ingredients.)

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the flour.
Blend.
Add seasoning (remove saucepan from heat).
Stir milk in slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.

title: granny's apricot slush
directions: In the 1-cup boiling water add tea bags and brew.
When dark, add sugar and all other ingredients.
Use one 6-ounce can of apricot brandy, then 3 1/2 cups of cold water.
Freeze.
This will semi-freeze.
Spoon into tall glass and top with ginger ale or 7-Up.
Wonderful holiday drink.

title: grandma poston's corn bread dressing
directions: Grease a large pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Makes the most moist corn bread dressing you have ever eaten.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add vegetables that are cut up.
Season and put on lid and turn burner on low.
Cook until tender. Stir occasionally.

title: tuna salad
directions: Add curry powder and salt to mayonnaise.
Drain and flake tuna and mix with celery and choice of fruit.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Chill 2 hours.
When ready to serve, add slivered, toasted almonds.
Serve on salad greens.

title: old fashion potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in small chunks and cook.
Drain off water and set aside.
Then add salt and pepper to mashed potatoes.
Add mayonnaise and mustard, then chopped pickles, onion and eggs.

title: chicken jubilee
directions: Place chicken skin side up in broiler.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drizzle with margarine.
Broil until brown.
Place in baking pan, standing chicken pieces on end.
Add drippings from broiler pan to baking pan.
Combine sauce, drained peaches and cherries, sliced onion and chili sauce.
Spoon over chicken.
Add one cup of combined peach and cherry drainings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Thicken sauce if desired.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Place 1/2 the bread cubes in bottom. Place 1/2 mushrooms on bread. Combine chopped veggies with mayonnaise. Spread 1/2 of this mixture over mushrooms. Repeat layers: bread, mushrooms and veggie mixture. Mix milk, eggs and seasonings and pour over layers. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Before baking, pour soup on top. Sprinkle with crumbs or cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until brown.

title: sausage-cabbage supper
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Place mixture in casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook on High 7 to 9 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Stir before serving.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix
cake
according to directions and bake.
While cake is baking,
mix
Jell-O as directions read.
Spoon Jell-O over cake which came right out of oven.
Top with cans of cherry pie filling and chill cake.
Serve cake with Cool Whip.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Grease cake pan, shake sugar and cinnamon mix around pan to coat all sides and bottom.
Save remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Mix first five ingredients well, then alternate sugar and cinnamon mixture with layers of cake batter until used up.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Simmer 10 minutes; gradually
stir in salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup. Add sour cream, but do not allow to boil or will curd. Serve over noodles, cooked. Serves 12.

title: fried spinach
directions: Heat oil in large pot or skillet.
Saute slivered garlic in oil; add spinach.
Toss repeatedly 2 to 3 minutes, until spinach is wilted.
Add beaten egg and toss thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Bring soup, water and onion to a boil in saucepan.
Add rice; cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in the thawed broccoli. Prepare 2 to 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and put half of the mixture in it.
Spread the chicken and cover with cheese.
Put the remaining rice mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese comes to the top and browns.

title: sirloin with new orleans butter sauce
directions: Dry the meat
with
a paper towel.
Spread 1 tablespoon butter on both sides.
Place in dish.
Microwave on High for 1 minute. Turn meat over.
Microwave
on
High
to 2 minutes longer depending
on doneness desired (3 minutes for rare or 6 minutes for
well done).
Remove meat onto cutting board.
Add remaining butter,
lemon juice, parsley and Worcestershire to the pan, stirring.
Microwave
at High for 1 minute.
Stir up juices from the dish.
Pour over steak.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Cut into thin slices to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stir-fry chicken and pepper
directions: In medium bowl, toss chicken with soy sauce and cornstarch. Put 1 tablespoon oil in hot wok or large skillet.
Add chicken mixture, stirring to separate pieces as it cooks.
Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove chicken from wok.
Add rest of oil to wok. Add garlic and peppers; stir-fry for 3 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Sift together all ingredients.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Combine all and spread in 9 x 13-inch.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 cup melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil in a large skillet about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove to plate.
Add onion rings to skillet.
Saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Reserve.

title: billygoat cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly, adding nuts and dates last.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: rua's "better" carbonara
directions: Saute Pancetta in olive oil for 3 minutes.
Add peppers and onions, saute until onions begin to brown.
Add cream, nutmeg, 1/2 parsley and twist of pepper.
Bring cream to simmer and stir. Cook for 2 minutes.
Cook pasta so that it is ready when sauce is finished.
The sauce will not hold well, move quickly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Into a greased baking dish (8 1/2 x 11-inch), layer the bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over these ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit combo
directions: Combine pudding and reserved pineapple juice. Mix well.
Mix fruit.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and mix gently.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 8 x 12 dish. Put foil over dish and put in freezer until set. Take out of freezer and serve.

title: easy brown bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add 1 cup boiling water and 2 cups cold water.
Add yeast and let rise a little.
Now add oil and flour.
Knead 20 minutes.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Knead.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Make into loaves (makes 4 loaves).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar and oil.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add sifted dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini, vanilla and nuts.
Fills 2 large loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hamburger slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and peppers and place in pan.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt
and
pepper
in saucepan and let come to boil.
Pour hot
liquid
over
cabbage mixture and let come to boil.
Add mustard and
place
in
hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: citrus-tea punch
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan; add tea bag. Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bag. Add fruit juices and sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves. Chill.
Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Add orange and lemon slices and lemon rind strips and mint, if desired.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix together eggs (beaten), mayonnaise, soup and onion.
Place layer of broccoli, layer of sauce and
layer of cheese (about 3 layers).
Top with crushed crackers and pats of butter.
Bake in oven until thoroughly heated and browned.
