title: marie ellzey's cornbread recipe
directions: Pour oil in bowl.
Break eggs in and beat with spoon.
Mix all dry ingredients together and alternate with milk in this mixture. Grease skillet or baking dish and heat it in 350° oven while mixing.
Pour in hot dish and cook 30 minutes or until brown.

title: jamaica barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into jar.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 1 3/4 pints.

title: easy sand tarts(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Stir in vanilla. Add salt and flour and mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Shape into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly on cookie sheets, then roll in additional powdered sugar, if desired.

title: bits and pieces cake
directions: Mix Dream Whip; set aside.
Mix vanilla, cream cheese and powdered sugar; add Dream Whip.
Break cake into pieces; add to the ingredients, then pour into rectangular cake pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Top with pie filling.
Cover with Saran Wrap; chill for 2 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine chicken (cut into pieces), 2 soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Place in 9 x 13 cooking dish.
In a small bowl, place cracker crumbs.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour over crackers.
Add poppy seeds.
Mix together.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut tops from peppers and remove seeds and veins.
Combine remaining ingredients with half the soup and spoon into peppers. Grease inside of crock-pot and stand peppers in bottom.
Spoon over remaining soup.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 hours on low or use a Dutch oven; cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening or margarine, buttermilk and bananas.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: anise toast
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and anise seed.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° in a greased and floured bread pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan and slice into 16 slices (1/2-inch).
Place on buttered cookie sheet and return to oven for 5 minutes or until bottoms are light brown.
Turn over and bake 5 minutes more.
(It may take 10 minutes on each side.)
Brush with butter.

title: italian breadsticks
directions: Mix olive oil and garlic powder.
Bake breadsticks at 350° for 5 minutes.
Dip warm breadsticks into mixture.

title: micro potato wedges
directions: Add garlic, paprika and Parmesan cheese to melted oleo in low glass dish (micro).
Dip wedges in mixture.
Arrange cut side down in dish; cover with paper towel.
Micro 10 to 12 minutes, turning halfway through.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter with sugar.
When light and fluffy, add eggs one at a time.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture alternately with juice, milk, vanilla, rind, cranberries and nuts. Line muffin tins with paper liners.
Fill three-fourths full with batter.
Bake in preheated 375° to 385° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until muffins test done.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine and knead into confectioners sugar.
Roll in balls and chill.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Put toothpick in top of balls and dip in chocolate and then refrigerate.

title: jello pinwheels
directions: Lightly spray 8 or 9-inch square pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix gelatin with water in 2-quart microwaveable bowl. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: clarence's candy
directions: Line a fudge pan with wax paper.
Make sure the wax paper is long enough to cover over 2 edges of the pan.
Combine sugar, water, butter and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil until forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Pour this in the lined pan and let it cool until hard.
Then, holding onto the edges of the wax paper, lift it out of the pan and place on counter top.

title: chicken breasts florentine
directions: Coat both sides of chicken breasts with flour.
In 1/4 cup hot butter in medium skillet, over medium heat, saute breasts 5 to 10 minutes on each side.
Add broth, simmer, covered, for 10 minutes until tender.
Remove to plate.
To skillet add 1/4 cup flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg; stir until smooth, add milk, then cream a little at a time.
Return to heat.
Over medium heat, bring to boil, stirring constantly, reduce heat, simmer 3 minutes.
In small bowl, beat egg yolk, stir in some hot sauce, mix well, return to saucepan, add grated cheese; stir over low heat until just thickened, do not boil.
Cook spinach, drain well.
Return to pan, mix with 1 cup cheese sauce.
Layer spinach mixture in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts in single layer on top.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; broil for a few minutes to brown.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in pan.
Add eggs and buttermilk or sweet milk-vinegar mixture.
In saucepan, bring water, oleo, oil and cocoa to boil.
Pour mixture into flour and sugar.
Mix well.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into graham cracker crust.

title: janet's sausage dressing
directions: Break hard bread into small pieces.
Break up raw sausage into small pieces.
Add onion and celery.
Pour hot broth or hot water over and mix until thoroughly dampened.
Should be "wet" but not soupy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into greased casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: gram's baked beans
directions: Pick over beans and wash.
Soak in water overnight.
In morning, parboil beans until they boil; remove from heat.
In a bean pot, place onion in bottom, then add drained beans (save liquid), salt, sugar, molasses and salt pork on top.
Fill pot with bean water to cover salt pork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 300° for 5 to 6 hours, adding bean water, if needed.

title: mini garlic sticks
directions: Combine butter, minced garlic and chopped chives.
Unroll breadsticks and spread with butter mixture.
Cut strips crosswise into quarters.
Twist strips and place in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: no bake peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter and Karo syrup together, then add powdered sugar and powdered milk.
Roll them in long roll and wrap with wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine celery, both peppers and onions.
Add vinegar, sugar, 2 cups water, celery seed and salt.
Bring this mixture to a boil and simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
Blend flour, dry mustard and turmeric in 1/2 cup cool water.
Add this mixture and corn to the batch.
Cook, with stirring, for 5 minutes.
Pack into hot half-pint jars.
Close and process for 20 minutes in boiling water.
Cool and store in cool place.

title: richard's cole slaw
directions: Grate first 4 ingredients; toss all lightly.
Add 5 tablespoons mayonnaise or add to taste.
Add salt, if desired.

title: white fish salad
directions: Chop celery and drain well.
Add to tuna, white fish and decrusted white bread.
Then add mayonnaise.
Serve on crackers and garnish with green olives.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate before serving. (Increase the amount of Miracle Whip if you want a dip consistency.)

title: easy bake beans kahlua
directions: Mix and stand overnight.
Bake at 375° for 50 or 60 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Prepare
pie
crust
and set aside.
Heat oven to 350°. In small mixer bowl, cream butter, eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and
flour;
add
to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts. Pour
into	unbaked pie crust and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.
Cool about 1 hour; serve warm.
Garnish with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350° and prepare pie crust as directed on package. Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg and beat until smooth. Set aside. Reserve hot fudge packet from brownie mix for topping. Combine brownie mix, oil, 1 tablespoon water and remaining 2 eggs; beat with spoon. Spread 1/2 cup brownie mixture in pie crust. Spoon and carefully spread cream cheese mixture over brownie layer. Top with remaining brownie mixture; spread evenly. Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until center is puffed and crust is golden brown. Microwave the hot fudge for 30 seconds and add 1 tablespoon water. Drizzle over pie. Store in the refrigerator.

title: sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze in ice cream freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: lentil soup ("masoor daal")(a soup from india)
directions: *Ginger-Garlic Paste:
If desired, 1 clove of garlic + 1 equal size of ginger needs to be ground to paste.

title: deviled cheese delight
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat with mixer until creamy. Chill.
Put in serving dish. Top with additional parsley. Serve with crackers or vegetable sticks.

title: pecan pie(kay's different)
directions: Beat sugar and baking
powder into egg whites.
Stir in crumbs and pecans.
Pour into a greased pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: microwave fresh corn-on-the-cob
directions: Place corn, water and butter in a casserole.
Cook, covered, on Full power 6 to 8 minutes.
Rearrange corn halfway through the cooking time.
Keep corn covered until ready to serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Unroll crescent rolls, separate into triangles, place triangles on a baking sheet.
Press together seams to seal.
Bake 12-15 minutes.

title: crisp peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make a crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Do not beat.
Stir until it is all blended.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven in floured Bundt pan.
Very light and moist; forms own glaze.
Makes a large cake.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water together until foamy, but not stiff. Pour in pecans and stir until all are well moistened.
Add mixture of sugar, salt and cinnamon to the pecans and stir until pecans are coated.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: liver spread
directions: Mix
well braunschweiger, cream cheese,
pickle,
onion and Dijon style mustard.
Chill until firm
enough
to handle. With oiled hands shape in 1 or 2 logs.
Roll in parsley.
Wrap tight and refrigerate overnight.

title: asparagus entree
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic in butter until soft.
Add pepper and asparagus.
In bowl, beat eggs; add rice and cottage cheese.
Mix well and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread vegetable mixture over top.
Heat through; do not let dry out.

title: bean dip
directions: Layer all the ingredients in order listed.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until the cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook sausage, stirring frequently until no longer pink.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place on pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press together and form crust, around the edge.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over crust (drained). Top with thawed potatoes, peppers, green onions and cheese.
Stir eggs, milk, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Pour evenly over pizza. Sprinkle with parmesan.
Bake 20 minutes or until eggs are set and crust is golden.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco, sugar, add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and soda; add to creamed mixture with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add coconut and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add nuts.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans. Bake 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost.

title: filled date bars
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, bring dates, raisins, sugar and water to a boil.
Boil together for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, mix margarine, brown sugar, flour, oats, soda and salt with electric mixer on lowest speed until mixture is crumbly.
Pat half the crumb mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread the cooked date filling over that, then top with the rest of the crumb mixture, patting it down lightly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 15 oblong bars.

title: chicken breasts and dried beef
directions: Wrap chicken breasts around beef (about 2 slices on each). Wrap 1 slice bacon around rolled chicken breast.
Put in casserole and cover with sauce made of soup and sour cream.
(Can refrigerate overnight.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
I broil and then turn and broil the under side at the end of the hour to make the bacon crisp.
Serve with rice or you can put Pepperidge Farm stuffing crumbs on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: meme's yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm, not hot. Mix yeast in 1/2 cup milk to dissolve. Mix sugar, salt, oil and eggs in remaining milk. Add yeast mixture. Mix thoroughly, then add enough flour to make a stiff batter. Beat real well each time you add more flour. Cover. Let rise until it doubles. Roll out on floured board. Do not roll out too thin or work in too much flour. Cut or pinch into rolls and place in lightly greased muffin tins. Brush with melted butter on top of dough. Let rise again until double. Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: pickled beans and corn
directions: Cook beans 10 minutes or until they can be mashed between fingers.
Let cool; pack in sterilized quart jars.
Cover with the mixture as follows.
Heat the salt, water and vinegar and pour over corn or beans.
Seal.
Put in cool place until pickled.
You might have to make added liquid, depending on how tight the food is packed.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Soak bread in the milk.
Combine with ground beef, egg, salt, garlic salt, pepper, oregano, Parmesan cheese and chives or green onion and make into balls.
Brown in Crisco oil.
Add tomato sauce, water, Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and oregano.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: presbyterian punch
directions: Make a sugar syrup by boiling the water and sugar for 3 minutes. Add everything except the ginger ale and freeze.
About 1/2 hour before serving, place frozen base in punch bowl and let thaw until slushy. Add ginger ale and serve.
Yields 50 to 60 cups.

title: hilda's beans
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: poor man's lobster no. 2
directions: Bring to a boil and drop fish in; cook until fish flakes.
Do not eat vegetables.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork mix first 4 ingredients.
In separate dish heat remaining ingredients. Combine 2 mixtures, stirring with fork until well blended.
Then with hands, mold dough into a ball. Chill at least 15 minutes before using.
Makes four one crust 9-inch pies, or two double crusts.
Can be frozen until ready to use in pie size portions.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, bacon, milk, soup and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: baby food loaf cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a tube or Bundt pan.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 1 1/4 cups warm water; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Place 1 cup warm water in mixing bowl and add shortening, sugar and salt.
Add yeast mix and flour to make a good, not too stiff dough.
Let rise; punch down and make rolls. Let rise to double and bake quick.

title: pecans dreams
directions: Mix as listed;	roll into balls and bake in a 200° oven until they turn
color.
While
hot,
roll
in 4x sugar; again while cool.

title: orange sauce
directions: Melt butter and add all ingredients except orange segments. Stir until smooth.
Simmer gently until clear.
Add segments and serve over meat or poultry.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: magic popovers
directions: Put ingredients in bowl; beat with spoon until slightly bubbly.
Batter will be lumpy.
Fill well-greased metal or Pyrex custard cups or muffin tins (Teflon without greasing) about 2/3 full.
Place in cold oven; set oven at 425°.
Do not peek for 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 huge popovers in large Pyrex custard cups or about 12 small ones.

title: quick teri hamburger and cabbage
directions: Fry ground beef in a large skillet until brown.
Pour off fat. Cut cabbage into 1-inch cubes and soak in water.
Add sugar and soy sauce in the skillet with beef and add the cabbage pieces on top.
Add 3/4 cup of water.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender, about 12 minutes.
Stir while it cooks twice.
Serve with rice.

title: naan bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and place in a deep bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour in eggs, milk and yogurt.
Stir until well blended.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Grease a large bowl with butter.
Coat dough in a bowl with butter. Cover and let sit for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Preheat broiler. Divide dough into 8 pieces and pat into teardrop shape, about 1/4-inch thick.
Broil Naan Bread 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in the butter.
Reduce heat and add soup, rice, chicken, milk and almonds (optional).
Mix well.
Pour chicken mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare stuffing as stated on package.
Spread stuffing over the top and heat through in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 10.

title: cheese-beer fondue
directions: Toss flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Cut garlic in half and rub around fondue pot.
Heat beer in pot over low heat.
At high heat, add cheese, one cup at a time, stirring after each addition, until cheese is blended.
Stir in red pepper sauce.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Eat by spearing a cube with a fondue fork and dipping in the sauce.
Serves 4.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break lettuce.
Fry and crumble bacon.
Put on lettuce.
Add onion.
Cut up cauliflower and put on top of onion.
Then add Mozzarella cheese and mayonnaise.
Add Parmesan cheese.
May be made ahead and tossed just before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: To melted butter or margarine, add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and confectioners sugar; mix until well blended. Press into a 13 x 9 ungreased pan. Melt chocolate chips; pour and smooth over surface. Let set. Cut into bars.

title: old fashioned cranberry relish
directions: Quarter orange and lemon and remove seeds.
Quarter apple and core it.
Do not peel fruit.
Grind all fruit in food grinder. Stir in sugar and cloves.
Place in covered nonmetal container and cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 2 days before serving.
Keeps 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Yields:
3 cups.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Cook pork chops, onion and bell pepper in Worcestershire sauce until done.
Add rice and gravy mix.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Pour all into a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken-stuffing bake
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on the box. Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, chicken and broccoli.
Place 1/2 stuffing in an 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pat to form a crust.
Pour the chicken mixture over the stuffing. Put the other 1/2 of the stuffing on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until heated through. This recipe can easily be doubled.

title: chocolate-walnut fudge
directions: In
a small bowl, microwave butter and milk on High for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.	Stir and set aside.

title: chewies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add brown sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour and nuts all at one time.
Mix well by hand.
Pour in greased and foil-lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 24 squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Mix in eggs and milk.
Shape into loaf; cover with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: u.s. 31 barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Add cabbage; simmer for about 20 minutes.
Stir often. Seal in canning jar, or keeps well in covered jar in fridge for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and pineapple.
Put in 2 large lightly greased pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool before removing from pans.

title: clam fritters
directions: Clean clams; drain and chop.
Beat eggs until light; add milk and flour, mixed and sifted with baking powder.
Then add chopped clams and season highly with salt and pepper.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until golden brown.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, brown the meat lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
Skim off the fat.
Thicken with flour and water.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: achy breaky cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cooled, poke numerous holes in cake with straw.
Combine milk and sauce until smooth and pour over cooled cake.
Ice cake with Cool Whip. Sprinkle crushed Butterfingers over top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: parfait pie
directions: Drain fruit; reserve syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup; heat to boiling.
Add gelatin; dissolve.
Add cold water.
Cut ice cream into 6 pieces; add to hot mixture.
Stir until melted. Chill until mixture thickens.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into vanilla cookie crust.
Chill until firm.

title: food processor biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Grease a 7 inch skillet or you can use a 9-inch cake pan. Combine all the ingredients in the bowl of a food processor, fitted with the steel blade.
Process for 15 to 20 seconds.
The dough will be sticky but do not add more flour.
Spoon the dough onto a floured surface.
Lightly dust the top of the dough with flour.
Gently knead about 10 times.
Pat or roll out to a thickness of 1/2 inch.
Cut with a 2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place in the skillet or cake pan.
Bake for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield: 8 biscuits.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease a long baking dish with margarine.
Drain pineapple in dish.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs and powdered milk with pineapple juice until smooth.
Cut toast into cubes.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Toss toast in margarine until coated.
Put buttered cubes over pineapple that has been covered with the juice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Mix and heat until bubbling.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: amigo pie
directions: Pour crust mixture into 9-inch pie pan (greased).
Pour hamburger mixture into middle of pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top of meat mixture for last 10 minutes.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Place mixture in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Lower 25 degrees for glass pan.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Place peeled and quartered potatoes in saucepan.
Cover with water. Bring to a boil, then cook until tender, about 8 to 10 more minutes.
Remove from heat and drain.
Remove garlic from potatoes and crush garlic with the flat of a knife or some other object.
Combine garlic with butter and green onions.
Add to potatoes.
Toss, then serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans, while draining chop the onion.
In a large bowl, stir first 4 ingredients until blended, add remaining ingredients, toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
I make this at least 48 hours before serving.
Stir several times a day.
When ready to serve, drain with slotted spoon.
Single serving is enough for 8 people.

title: quiche
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine sausage and cheese.
Place in pie shell.
Slightly beat 4 eggs and combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mash persimmons through colander (makes about 1 cup of pulp). Add melted butter to pulp.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in large pan at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown.
Use 11 x 14-inch pan.

title: venison steak
directions: Saute carrots, celery and onion in butter until tender; remove from pan.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dredge venison in flour mixture and brown in shortening on medium heat. Add sauteed vegetables, bay leaf and broth to meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Great over rice!
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tacos (with hidden vegetables)
directions: This also allows for variations in ingredients, amounts, it all works!

title: fried okra
directions: Wash okra and cut off the ends of the pods, cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Moisten slightly and shake in paper bag containing corn meal, salt and pepper.
Fry in hot bacon fat until golden brown.

title: citrus dream salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice concentrate.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 10.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Slice the entire batch of rolls in half.
Place ham and cheese on
bottom.
Spread
mayonnaise on top portion and put back together.
Mix
all
the
other ingredients together and pour over
the rolls.
(For better results, refrigerate overnight.) Then
bake
at 350° for 15 minutes.
This recipe will make 2 pans of rolls.

title: chocolate creme
directions: In small mixer bowl, blend milk, brandy, dessert topping mix and coffee.
Beat in frosting on low speed.
Beat on high speed until soft peaks form.
Pour into demitasse.
Chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: super stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake for 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over noodles.

title: shrimp tart delight(appetizer)
directions: Mix and put into tart shells, which can be bought in the bread section of your grocery store.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes. Yields 24 tarts.

title: orange banana slush
directions: Boil sugar in water until dissolved. Mix in lemonade and orange juice. Run bananas through blender with pineapple juice and add to mixture. Stir well and freeze. Remove to refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before serving. Pour into punch bowl and stir in Sprite. Can keep frozen about 3 weeks.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix roll of crackers (crushed) and put on top. Put slices of margarine on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef curry
directions: Cook beef strips in nonstick skillet 5 minutes until there is no pink.
Remove and keep warm.
Cook onion and garlic on low until transparent.
Add carrots, green pepper and celery stirring until tender-crisp.
Add apples cooking until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan and stir in cornstarch and all spices as well as broth. Stir and heat until thick.
Return beef and vegetables to skillet; add sauce and cook 5 minutes. Remove stick and serve with favorite starch dish.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti on top of stove according to directions; drain. Stir in butter.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form mixture into a crust in a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Crush potato chips real fine.
Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and coat with crushed chips.
Lay in baking pan or roll up each breast jelly roll fashion.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until browned.

title: whisper cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Beat the eggs and oil together in large bowl.
Add cake mix and mix well.
Add dissolved gelatin; mix.
Put batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle coconut and pecans over cake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put peanuts, syrup and water in a thick saucepan.
Cook until it turns a light caramel, stirring all the time.
Remove from heat.
Add wax; stir until all wax has been melted.
Spread on foil paper; smooth out.
When cold, break in pieces.

title: continental chicken
directions: Place 2 slices of dried beef on each chicken breast and roll up.
Wrap each
rolled
breast
with
a
slice
of bacon. Place in a lightly
greased baking dish.
Cover with a mixture of soup, sour cream	and
flour.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 minutes. Serve over rice or hot, buttered noodles.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients for about 15 minutes or until thickened.
Add ham and simmer another 15 minutes.
Serve on hard rolls.
Sauce is also good on pork chops and boiled potatoes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Put fruit cocktail in blender and blend until pureed.
Add cream cheese, blending well.
Add Cool Whip and blend until completely mixed. Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Stir in maraschino cherries, distributing evenly.
If desired, add some of the liquid from the cherries or food coloring for color.
Freeze until firm. Cut into squares and serve.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Melt margarine 1 minute on High.
Add cocoa, vanilla, milk and sugar.
Beat vigorously.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Beat well.
Add nuts, stir until blended. Pour into buttered dish. Cool 30 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in cornbread mixture.
Bake according to directions.

title: swedish hash
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add vegetables, soup, 1/2 can of water, salt, pepper and rice.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cheese slices; return to oven and brown.

title: spicy pirate
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, salt, soy sauce, egg and flour.
Shape into bite size balls.
Brown in oil or shortening.
Make the sauce and pour over meatballs.

title: bayd bil batata (eggs and potato)(lebanese; international)
directions: Fry onions with 3 tablespoons shortening until they are tender; add over all the ingredients and fry until eggs are done. Serve in the morning as a breakfast or light dinner with pita bread.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar and set aside for 5 minutes.
Then mix with other ingredients very thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into rolls and place on a greased cookie sheet. Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Baking time may vary according to your oven.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Heat one inch of water in skillet with 1 tsp. salt and 2 T. vinegar to boiling. Add cabbage. Cover and heat to boiling; cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender-crisp. Drain. Fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and save 1 T. bacon drippings in skillet. Stir brown sugar and flour into bacon drippings. Add water, vinegar, salt, pepper, and onion. Cook, stirring frequently, about five minutes or until mixture thickens. Add bacon and cabbage to the sauce mixture. Stir together gently and heat through.

title: mexican tossed salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place cut-up chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and water; gently spoon over chicken.

title: artichoke chili-cheese dip
directions: Combine the chopped artichoke hearts, chopped chili peppers, cheese and mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.
Turn mixture into an 8-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips and breadsticks. Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: almond pine cones
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in a shallow pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often until almonds just begin to turn color. Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise; mix well. Add bacon, onion, dill weed and pepper; mix well. Cover and chill overnight.

title: cream of parisian vegetable soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 2 cups water.
In a pan melt margarine; then add onions and saute until they are slightly clear.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Add bouillon cubes and milk. Stir until thick and smooth.
Add vegetables (liquid and all), ham and white pepper.
Salt to taste.
Cook for a short time and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and use to baste chicken and ribs or use for barbecue sandwiches.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake one crust for 2 or 3 minutes (just long enough to keep it from becoming soggy from filling).
Drain apples and reserve juice (for part of the 1 cup juice).
Combine cornstarch, apple juice and Sweet 'N Low.
Heat until boiling and mixture thickens.
Spread apple slices in partially baked crust and pour cooked mixture over the fruit.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg over apples and dot with margarine.
Top with second crust.
Make small slashes in crust to let steam escape.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cover with foil during last part of baking if crust is getting too brown.

title: fat-free spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Cut up tomatoes, cucumbers and bell pepper.
Add to spaghetti; add dressing.
Mix well and refrigerate before serving.
Serves 15 or more.
To serve less, use 1/2 the recipe.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables slightly and drain well.
Place in baking dish and add water chestnuts (I slice them).
Add chunks of Velveeta cheese (probably about 1/2 pound, I never measure).
Add 2 tablespoons of melted butter to vegetables.
Mix remaining butter with crushed crackers and place over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix grated cheese with cracker crumbs.
Add liquid from asparagus to mushroom soup.
Put layer of crumbs and cheese in bottom of casserole; layer of asparagus; layer of eggs and layer of nuts.
Cover with mushroom mixture.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Melt butter and pour on each layer and on top, ending with cheese and crumb.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together in a large mixing bowl.
Add 1 can Pet milk.
Add 4 beaten eggs.
Mix in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Melt oleo in microwave or soften at room temperature.
Combine with other ingredients.
Add 2 cups chopped nuts.

title: kool kake
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed, omitting cold water.
Let sit at room temperature.
Bake cake using a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool. Poke holes in cake.
Pour Jell-O over all.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip before serving.

title: lemon barbecue sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add water, lemon juice, salt, sugar, thyme, pepper and hot sauce.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Allow to cool, then use as a basting sauce for beef, pork or chicken.

title: chocolate cake with buttercream icing
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round baking pans.
In
a small bowl, stir together cocoa and water until smooth, set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir together flour, baking soda
and salt; add to shortening mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in cocoa mixture and beat well.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center come outs clean.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pans to wire rack to cool completely.
Frost with buttercream frosting.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter, sugar, pinch of salt and vanilla.
Pour into square pan.
Press out.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. In large bowl, at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients until blended, constantly scraping bowl with spatula.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Stir in carrots and coconut.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove cake from pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: cranberry souffle salad
directions: In saucepan, combine 1 1/4 cups of the orange juice, cranberry sauce and gelatin.
Cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in remaining orange juice.
Transfer to medium mixing bowl.
Beat whipping cream to soft peaks; fold into gelatin mixture.
Apply seal; chill 4 to 6 hours or until set.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Heat butter or oil; saute onions and remove.
Add beef (1/3 at a time), brown and remove.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon fat. Stir in flour, meat extract paste and tomato paste.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add Burgundy, beef, onion, pepper, herbs and mushrooms.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and bake for 2 1/2 hours.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place 2 pieces of aluminum foil crisscrossed on the bottom of a roast pan.
Place 1/2 of the onion soup mix on the foil.
Put the chuck roast on top of the soup mix.
Sprinkle the rest of soup mix over the top of the roast.
Pour the undiluted can of mushroom soup over the roast.
Place the potatoes and carrots around the roast and bring up the ends of the foil and seal.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: overnight crock-pot roast
directions: You will need a cooking bag.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, oleo and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Then add baking soda, stir and pour over popcorn in bowl.
Spread on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes while the mixture is baking.

title: my style chili
directions: Brown meat in 12-inch skillet; drain grease.
In a slow cooker or
Dutch
oven,
add
meat, tomatoes, paste, beans and spices. Dice
peppers
and onion.
Cook on high until boiling starts, then on
low-medium
for
hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
In slow
cooker
cook on high until boiling starts, then on
low
for 3
to
hours, stirring every 30 minutes. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Dice tomato and chop onions.
Mix these three ingredients; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, season to taste and mix mayonnaise and corn mixture. Great with anything!

title: mexican tortilla rolls
directions: Mix the first six ingredients and spread thinly onto tortillas.
Roll tortillas, then roll tortillas in damp paper towels.
Place in a large sandwich bag and seal tightly.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Cut up	chicken
and
place
in a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish. Pour soy
sauce
on
top.
Bake
at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or microwave on Medium-high until done (9 to 10 minutes per pound, rest 5).
Baste soy sauce on top of chicken to keep moist.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Put cabbage leaves in boiling water until limp.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Place in cabbage leaves and roll up.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage rolls.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add onions and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add tomatoes and okra. Heat for 10 minutes.

title: snicker bars(candy)
directions: Melt together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Add all ingredients except cheese to the pan the hamburger was browned in and heat slowly to make sure all is well blended. A small amount of water can be added if the mixture seems too thick. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for about 35-45 minutes. Top with cheese and return to oven for 5-10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set overnight. Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased mold. Freeze overnight.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Roll meat into 2-inch balls.
Should make about 10.
Fry in vegetable oil until brown. You can use with marinara sauce or by themselves.
These can also be frozen for later use.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except eggs) into a bowl.
Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each egg.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: zesty new potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until just tender.
Drain and cut in chunks. Add celery and scallions. Add salad dressing and toss lightly. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 180 calories each.

title: mrs. litke's seafood delight
directions: Spray heavy pan with Pam.
Saute vegetables in a little oil for a few minutes, until tender.
Add celery soup mixed with milk. Lavish with basil, dill weed and lemon pepper.
Stir in crab meat. Simmer until vegetables are to desired tenderness.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and celery in butter 15 minutes or until water evaporates.
Add another 1 to 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle flour over top.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Frost with chocolate pudding.
Refrigerate until pudding is set.

title: cocktail crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: my vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in the bottom of a big heavy pot with a little oil. Add knuckle; cover with water and simmer 4 or 5 hours with onion and celery.
Cool and remove bones and vegetables.
Cut meat into bite sized pieces and put back into pot.
Add potatoes, vegetables, pepper, tomatoes, peppercorns, salt, soup mix, rice, parsley and celery.
Simmer 20 minutes after returns to boil.
Add okra.
When okra is thawed, turn off fire.
At same time, put in some chopped cabbage and cover.
Remaining heat will cook okra and cabbage before soup is cool enough to eat.

title: greek olive relish
directions: Process the first 3 ingredients in a food processor until very finely minced.
Add the next 4 ingredients and process for about 10 seconds.
Serve with Feta and water crackers.
Makes hors d'oeuvres for 6.

title: diet lasagna
directions: Use a 2-quart casserole.
Layer string beans, hamburg, cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Contains approximately 175 calories per cup.
Serves six.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken; take out bones and fat.
Chop.
Cream together chicken, celery, onion, water chestnuts, soups and sour cream.
Add seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour in sprayed baking dish.
Top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: clam dip
directions: Melt butter and fry onions until transparent.
Add juice from 1 can of clams and lemon juice.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Mix in all other ingredients except cheese.
Grease pan or pie plate. Add mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers or pumpernickel bread.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Put in refrigerator.
Roll graham crackers to make crumbs.
Add powdered sugar and melted butter and mix.
Line a large baking dish with one-half of the cracker mixture.
Put in refrigerator.
Cream together cheese and sugar, then add vanilla and Jell-O mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into crumb-lined baking dish and top with remaining cracker mixture. Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: mom's egg pie(quick, easy and good)
directions: Whisk eggs, milk, sugar and eggs. Add the rest of the ingredients in order given and mix well. Pour mixture into a 9 inch pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until pie is golden brown (knife in center comes out clean).

title: "pug's" chow-chow
directions: Combine vegetables and salt; stir well.
Cover and let stand 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
Drain well.

title: fruit special
directions: Cook over medium heat until it comes to a full boil, stirring constantly until rhubarb is soft.
Cool.
Add crushed pineapple. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: sausage-stuffed butternut squash
directions: Place squash, cut side down, in a greased shallow baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until squash is easily pierced. Meanwhile, saut sausage, which has been removed from the casing, until brown and crumbly.
Add onion and garlic and saut until onions are soft.
Stir in bread, parsley and eggs.
Remove from heat.
Turn squash, cut side up, and scoop out seeds.
With a fork, mash squash in the skin.
Spoon sausage mixture over squash. Replace in oven and bake another 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until blended; beat in eggs until well blended.
Add cocoa and vanilla, blending until smooth.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set in center.
Cool completely.
Cover top with Cool Whip.

title: paradise salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot cup of jello.
Add 1 cup of cold water.
Let partly congeal, then stir in all the other ingredients.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Use your favorite topping.

title: shrimp ala creole
directions: Clean shrimp and boil 5 minutes. saving stock.
Using an iron skillet, make a roux by heating oil and flour, stirring constantly until well browned.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Add shrimp and pepper.
Stir until shrimp are covered with roux.
Add paste and green peppers.
Stir 15 minutes.
Pour in 1 cup of hot shrimp stock and cook 15 minutes.
Cook 1 hour slowly.
Serve over rice.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet, stirring to crumble meat. Drain.
Add macaroni, tomato sauce and next 2 ingredients, stir. Cook over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes, stirring.
Stir in cheese.

title: party cheese rolls
directions: Combine cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into one large ball or roll.
Chill until firm.
Slice.

title: waffle mix
directions: Beat eggs.
Put soda into milk.
Combine flour, salt and sugar together.
Pour egg mixture in slowly.
Add melted butter.
Blend well.

title: toffee bars
directions: Combine butter, granulated and brown sugar in a large bowl. Cream with mixer for 1 minute.
Add egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute longer.

title: fudge candy
directions: Butter 3 plates.
Mix sugar, cream, salt and vanilla.
Cook on high; bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add butter and boil for 10 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Then pour into plates.
Let cool and cut into 3-inch squares.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat the cream cheese and margarine until fluffy; add sugar, 1/2 at once then the other 1/2.
Ice cake when completely cool and add chopped nuts to side and top.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix together and store in fridge.
Mix with salad greens, croutons, fresh shrimp and can of artichoke hearts.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let rise then roll out.
Place salami, pepperoni and onion and pepper and cheese in layers.
Roll up as a jelly roll.
Pinch ends so filling does not fall out.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes. Brush with butter to stay soft.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: Mix fruit and 1 cup sugar together; let sit.
Melt butter in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients together and pour batter over melted butter.
Pour fruit over batter.
Crust will come to the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim excess fat from meat. Cut into 2 x 1/2-inch strips. Combine 1/4 cup flour, salt and paprika.
Coat meat with flour mixture.
In skillet, brown beef strips in cooking oil. Remove meat and set aside. Cook onion, garlic and mushrooms in skillet drippings until onion is tender but not brown.
Blend in the 2 tablespoons flour.
Add beef consomme, wine and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat.
Heat until bubbly. To remaining sauce in skillet, blend in sour cream and parsley. Return browned beef strips to skillet.
Heat through.
Do not boil. Serve over hot cooked noodles. Serves 4.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt and egg yolks. Add milk. Lastly, add beaten egg whites. Cook until thickened. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Put in ice cream maker.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Heat soup and add cheese to melt.
In casserole dish, layer asparagus, then eggs, then soup mixture.
Can make as many or as few layers as desired.
Cover top of casserole with bread crumbs. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.

title: soft sugar cookies - german
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk and sour cream.
Add approximately 8 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Can be doubled.

title: jicama (he'ke me) salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, jicama and onions. In small jar, combine balance of ingredients except lettuce. Cover and shake. Pour over vegetables; toss. Cover and refrigerate for several hours, spooning dressing over salad occasionally.

title: salad of distinction
directions: Juice of pineapple and enough water to make 1 pint of liquid. Let the jello and liquid slightly mold before adding the grated carrots and crushed pineapple.
Mix all together and mold in a large mold or individual molds.
Serve on lettuce.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Slice cheese and chop onion and green pepper while cooking macaroni as directed on package.
Drain well in a colander.
In a 2 1/2-quart baking dish, layer 1/3 of each, starting with macaroni, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, small dots of butter and then cheese.
Repeat.
Pour milk over top layer of cheese. Bake at 400° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Top layer of cheese will be brown and crusty.

title: mom's egg custard
directions: Heat milk and butter to boiling point in a saucepan. Beat whole eggs lightly in a bowl.

Add sugar and vanilla to egg mixture. Stir in milk. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and cook until pie is firm. If pie browns too fast, cover the entire pie with foil until pie is done.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Blend well.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place in oblong dish.
Freeze until ready to serve. Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: swiss asparagus casserole
directions: Combine 4 tablespoons butter, salt, paprika and flour.
In small saucepan over low heat, blend until smooth.
Add milk gradually.
Stir until smooth and add soup and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to soup mixture along with pimiento and eggs. Alternate layers of asparagus and sauce in lightly greased casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey salad
directions: Pour dressing over tomatoes, mushrooms, zucchini, olives, red pepper, carrot and onion.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Toss vegetable mixture with greens.
Top with turkey and cheese. Serve with additional dressing, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. Great way to use leftover holiday turkey!

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Cream until light and fluffy. Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with the Orange Crush.
Add flavoring.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sausage pizza
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together the first 6 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients to mixture; blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: relish delish
directions: Mix salt and cabbage; let stand 3 hours.
Squeeze liquid from all vegetables.
Mix vinegar, sugar, hot peppers and celery together.
Add to vegetables; stir until mixed well.
Put into jars.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Will keep in refrigerator for 6 months.
Jars do not have to be sealed.
Good immediately, but better in a few days.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: bacon-wrapped chicken breasts
directions: Place a slice of beef on the underside of the chicken breasts. Reserve extra slices for future use.
Wrap bacon around both, making a roll.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream and sherry; spoon over chicken.
Cover; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover; bake another 30 minutes, or until brown.
May be made ahead and refrigerated until time to bake. Serve with steamed rice.

title: crab ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and crab meat.
Shape into ball.
Cover with seafood cocktail sauce.
(Start with just enough cocktail sauce to cover ball; add more later, if desired.) Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Heat water and bouillon cube to boiling. Add broccoli and carrot and cook according to directions on broccoli box. Remove from heat. Don't drain. In pan that you are going to make soup in, make white sauce by melting margarine and slowly stirring in flour. Continue stirring while slowly adding milk. Continue stirring until lumps are gone. Stir soup in bowl until smooth. Add to milk. Stir. Add cheese, onion, Worcestershire, salt and pepper. Cook on medium-low. Stir often until cheese is melted. Add broccoli and carrot mixture to this. Cook over low heat until thickens. Be careful or it will stick to pan. Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Heat muffins and ham separately in foil.
Set the oven to 350° for 7 minutes.

title: mexican chili dip
directions: Combine together in a crock-pot.
Heat at low temperature for 2 to 4 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Place juices in large coffee maker.
Place all other ingredients in basket and perk.
When cycle is completed, remove basket to prevent it from becoming too strong.

title: greek potato "fries"
directions: Clean potatoes. Cut lengthwise into 8 wedges. Place into a bowl of ice water for 30 minutes. Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Toss potatoes with oil. Place on oiled baking sheet, skin side down. Sprinkle oregano and pepper over potatoes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Cut like biscuits, slash and fold over.
Bake at 475° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine garlic, basil, parsley and pine nuts in food processor.
Continue to process and add oil in slow, steady stream.
Stop machine.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Process for a few seconds to combine.
Serve promptly over favorite pasta.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Mix water, oil, honey, salt and yeast in large bowl.
(I use Dutch oven.)
Stir gently.
Add 10 cups flour and squish together thoroughly.
Turn dough onto floured kneading board and knead in last 2 cups flour.
Knead for at least 20 minutes, until smooth and elastic.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until thick and reduced by one-half.

title: gingerbread
directions: Dissolve
soda	in
boiling water.
Mix dry ingredients (except sugar).
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Add dry ingredients.	Pour in water and mix.	Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: different macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add enough bacon grease to flavor.
Microwave 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese thoroughly melts.
Or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix before serving.

title: crab stuffed jalapenos
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove and discard pulp and seeds; rinse carefully.
In a large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except for breading mixture.
Stuff peppers with crab mixture; press remaining stuffing around pepper.
Set aside to prepare breading mixture.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cake is done; let cool.
Frost with frosting.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Mix together and cook slowly.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into slices 1/4-inch thick.
Mix batter together and dip onion slices into it.
Fry in deep fat until browned.

title: pecan balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into balls. Put balls on pan covered with wax paper. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except blackberries in bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in blackberries carefully.
Pour into well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm. Top with ice cream or milk.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix all of above.
Grease pan; put in berries and batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple and soften the cheese.
Combine all of the ingredients, but use only 1 cup of the nuts.
Chill until firm enough to shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll balls in the remaining cup of nuts.
Best made a day ahead of serving.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, pour large can crushed pineapple with juice. Spread over cake and cool.
In large bowl, mix pudding and milk. Beat until thick.
Fold in about 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.
Put in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing.
Boil and debone chicken.
Layer chicken and dressing.
Pour soup over top.
Top with dressing and pour broth over everything.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix in order given, diluting frozen orange juice concentrate with the amount of water called for on can.
Add sherbet and ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 40 servings.

title: all-purpose pastry
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter with a knife or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Gradually add egg yolks and ice water until a firm ball is formed.
Do not overwork dough.
Seal the dough in plastic wrap and chill for at least 30 minutes before rolling out.
When chilled, roll out to about 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface 2 inches larger than pan into which it will be fitted.
When fitted into pan, trim edges and finish as directed.
Makes enough for 1 double-crust pie.
(We froze the second crust.)

title: dutch apple crumb pie
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Mix with apples and raisins.
Pour in crust.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread out 1 can of crescent rolls in bottom of pan.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread mixture over crust and cover with second package of rolls.
Beat egg white with a fork until frothy.
Brush on top of rolls.
Lightly combine the margarine, sugar and cinnamon to crumbly consistency.
Crumble over top of crust and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24 servings.

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and keep in refrigerator (will keep for 5 to 6 weeks).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, salt and spices; mix together. Add small can of milk.
Combine with mashed potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until firm.

title: pasta with peas
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until tender; add peas and liquid.
Simmer until pasta is cooked.
Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Add pea mixture.
Serve with grated Italian cheese.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir into buttermilk. Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Cover and chill.
When ready to use, roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits with 2-inch cutter and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Dough will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen (2-inch) biscuits.

title: slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil together.
Pour over cut-up cabbage, green peppers, and carrots.

title: baked canned ham
directions: Stud ham with whole cloves over the entire surface.
Pat brown sugar thickly over entire surface.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: bead clay
directions: Mix flour, salt and cornstarch in bowl. Add warm water gradually until mixture forms a shape.
Knead.
Make beads; pierce with toothpicks and allow to dry.
Paint and string.
Seal, if desired.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until foamy.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 2 cups.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Warm oil; add other ingredients (not oyster crackers).
Stir. Pour over oyster crackers and mix.

title: guacamole fantastico(low fat dip recipes)
directions: Mix together and serve with baked tortillas or veggies.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell. Chill 3 hours. Top with strawberries and glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mushroom and zucchini toss
directions: In large saucepan, cook pasta.
Drain; return to pan and toss with butter.
Set aside.
In skillet, simmer mushrooms, zucchini, garlic, savory and salt until zucchini is tender-crisp.
Add tomato and cook just until heated.
Pour over pasta.
Add onion and toss.
Serve with cheese.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well after each addition.
Mix milk and cherry juice.
Add flour alternately with the liquid, beginning and ending with the flour.
Add vanilla.
Stir in half the cherries. Reserve the rest to garnish the top or use in frosting.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs well.
Add carrots and pineapple; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla last and beat well.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) cake pans at 350° for 45 minutes or in small loaf pans for 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring 3 times during cooking.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Using large bowl, mix together cole slaw, onion, sunflower seeds and almonds.
Crush noodles before opening, then add to cole slaw mixture.
Mix chicken packet (from noodles) with vinegar, oil and sugar.
Add to cole slaw mixture; mix well.

title: tortellini supper
directions: Cook tortellini according to directions, drain. In a skillet melt butter, cook mushrooms over medium heat stirring occasionally. When mushrooms are tender stir in tortellini and peas, continue cooking 3-5 minutes. Stir in 1 cup of cheese and salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: versatile cake
directions: Mix "wet" ingredients.
Add in "dry" ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured baking loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 1 hour plus, until done.
Test for doneness with knife.
Freezes well when cool.

title: pudding layer dessert
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crab and spinach roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Grease glass dish with butter or nonstick spray.
Dry chicken thoroughly.
Roll in sour cream.
Dip in herb stuffing; coat well. Place in dish.
Pour wine over chicken.
Bake slowly at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pizza pan cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease two 12-inch pizza pans. Cream the butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla in a large bowl. Add eggs; beat until light.
Combine soda and salt in a small bowl.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Divide dough in half.
Press each half evenly into pizza pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Cool completely in pans on wire racks.
Soften 1/2 gallon of ice cream; place evenly between the 2 cookies.
Freeze!

title: veal chops and potatoes(tangy)
directions: Pour olive oil in bottom of roasting pan. Arrange chops and potatoes in pan. Add seasonings. Add 5 or 6 hot cherry peppers (or less depending on taste) and a little of the cherry pepper oil. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and cook for 15 minutes.

title: chili blanco
directions: Cook and dice chicken. Make sure you have 10 cups of broth. (When I use chicken breasts or filets instead of a whole chicken, I put chicken bouillon cubes in broth to make it a bit richer.) In a skillet, saute onions in oil until tender. Add chilies, tomatoes, juice and seasonings. Mix thoroughly and cook about 10 minutes. Add to chicken broth. Add chicken and continue to simmer 1 hour. Add cooked rice about 30 minutes before done. Taste for salt. Garnish with grated cheese.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet until no pink remains; drain.
Add all ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes (I have made this with only one pound of ground beef and simmered it 15 minutes to cook off of the liquid; it was fine).
Line a lightly greased 13 x 9 pan with half the tortillas. Spoon half of the beef mixture on top of them, then sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Layer the remaining tortillas over the cheese and spoon on the remaining beef mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake another 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: spaghetti(italian)
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add next 9 ingredients. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti.
Cook until spaghetti is done, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir often so spaghetti won't stick.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Bring to a boil vinegar, beet juice, sugar, salt and beets. Serve warm or let cool.
Add chopped onions for a salad.

title: vichyssoise
directions: In saucepan, cook leeks and onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add potatoes, broth and 1 tablespoon salt.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Rub through a fine sieve.
Return to heat; add milk and light cream.
Season to taste.
Bring to a boil; cool.
Rub through very fine sieve.
Stir in whipping cream.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Garnish with chives.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sondra adkins' date nut bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350° .
Cut dates finely; put in bowl and sprinkle baking soda over them. Pour boiling water over this.
Let stand while mixing remainder of ingredients.

title: cocoa lite frosting
directions: In small saucepan combine butter, milk and cocoa.
Place over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Remove from heat, add to powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Makes 1 1/2 cups, enough to frost a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in 2 1/2-quart covered casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Drain excess grease and let cool for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: In a Dutch oven,
add
peas, water, ham hock, onion and carrot.
Bring to a boil
and simmer for about 1 hour.
Remove onion and carrot (leave
carrot if you wish).
Remove ham hock and let cool.
Add
bouillon
cubes
and chopped meat from ham hock. Simmer until peas are real tender and mushy.
Time will vary. Serve with corn bread and a little hot sauce.

title: tapioca spring fruit
directions: Cook all ingredients together until done, except Jell-O.
Add Jell-O after it's done.

title: zanny strawberry-wine slush
directions: In a blender container, combine the fresh strawberries, Sauterne, frozen limeade concentrate and ice cubes.
Blend until the mixture is smooth.
Add sugar if a sweeter flavor is desired. Serve immediately in stemmed glasses.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups of slush, equaling 5 (4 ounce) servings.

title: old-fashion pound cake
directions: Cream
the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at
a time.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour, flavorings and milk alternately until all are well mixed together.
Bake in a cold oven at
to
375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Insert a knife; when it comes out clean, cake is ready.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix together milk, powdered sugar, sour cream and Cool Whip. Break angel food cake into pieces and fold into mixture.
Top with strawberries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian chicken
directions: Saute onions, peppers and chili powder; add tomato sauce. Fry chicken dipped in flour.
Put chicken in sauce; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Cook shell noodles by package directions.
Drain.
Pour sauce over noodles.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Core and seed the bell peppers.
Cut into large pieces.
Seed all but 3 to 4 jalapenos. Pour vinegar into blender.
Add peppers and jalapenos. Blend until liquified.
Pour into a large pot (3 to 5-quart).
Add sugar and boil briskly for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add the Certo and food coloring. Return to heat and boil for 1 minute.
Pour into hot canning jars. Allow to cool and refrigerate.

title: cheesy macaroni soup
directions: Put water and salt in 3-quart saucepan and bring to a boil. Add macaroni.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and bring water to boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook for 5 minutes. Drain macaroni and vegetables.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Put fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Batter will rise during baking and cover the fruit (I like cherries or peaches best.)

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, flour, margarine, lemon juice and lemon extract. Mix well.
Beat egg whites separately until stiff, fold into other ingredients.
Pour into a baked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar and margarine. Add peanut butter, vanilla and eggs until well blended.

title: granola
directions: Combine all, except oil and honey, in a large bowl.
Mix oil and honey and pour over oat mix.
I add vanilla to oil and honey. Dried, diced fruit of any kind may be added, also sunflower seeds. Mix well.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in medium mixing bowl. Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice; toss with chicken and chill several
hours.
Spoon
onto
bed
of
lettuce
or
individual plates.
Sprinkle with pineapple and rest of almonds.

title: pink freeze
directions: Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add pineapple, cranberry sauce, nuts, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze 6 hours in loaf pan.
Slice to serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise, Hidden Valley Ranch mix and onion powder together; spread cheese mixture on cooled crust.
Layer grated vegetables on top of cheese mixture. Serve.

title: orzo provencal(makes 4 servings)
directions: In a medium bowl, place all ingredients except orzo and toss to combine.
Add orzo; stir to combine.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Cook over boiling water or in a heavy aluminum pan until thick.
Add butter.

title: mawmaw's meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, pepper, egg, mustard, salt and pepper. Add 2 tablespoons of condensed soup and crumbled toast. Mix well. Divide into 2 parts and pat into loaves. Fry on one side until bottom is half done, then flip. Add remaining tomato soup to tops and fry until done. Soup will form sauce. These may also be baked at 350° for 1 hour, adding soup topping after 30 minutes.

title: club pasta salad
directions: Prepare Ranch and Bacon Pasta Salad Mix according to directions. Stir in chicken, tomatoes, and cheese. Add additional Ranch dressing to taste.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix together.
Add 3 pounds thin sliced and cut into strips beef.
Let soak in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Remove from brine. Place on smoker racks.
Lightly sprinkle with garlic powder and Johnny salt.
Smoke 3 pans of chips for a period of 20 hours or until dry.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In nonmetal deep dish, combine the ingredients until dissolved. Add meat, pouring some over top, and refrigerate 36 to 48 hours, turning meat 3 to 4 times.
Remove meat.
Sprinkle lightly with flour (reserve 1 cup liquid marinade) and brown.
Add marinade plus 1/2 cup water and bake in 350° oven 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: coal miner soup
directions: Clean and cook peas.
Drain peas and keep the juice.
Put peas in food processor and chop up.
Put pea mixture back into cooking pot.
Add picante sauce, salt, pepper and garlic.
If too thick, add pea juice until you get a medium
mixture.

title: lizzies
directions: Put raisins in bowl.
Add bourbon.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 hour.
Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and clove.
In large bowl, put soften butter, brown sugar and beat.
Add eggs beat again.
Beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in raisins, pecans or walnuts, pineapple, cherries.
Drop by teaspoons rounded onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 15 minutes or until firm.
Makes 7-8 dozen and can be frozen.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Crumble with a fork Roquefort cheese.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, chives and fresh ground pepper.
Add, but do not beat the sour cream and buttermilk.
Do not mix in blender.
Refrigerate!! Scrumptious!!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well, but do not beat.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tirolean baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put them in a glass baking dish, bake at 350°F for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and nicely browned.

title: peach salad
directions: Put Jell-O in saucepan.
Pour pineapple and juice over this and heat enough to dissolve Jell-O.
Cool in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Add buttermilk.
Stir in well.
Let congeal a little more than add nuts and Cool Whip.
Stir well and put in refrigerator until firm.

title: texas goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni. While cooking the meat mixture, boil macaroni according to package directions (do not overcook; cook until firm), then add macaroni (including water) to meat mixture. Continue cooking for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with corn bread and green salad.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bring oleo to room temperature.
Spray tube pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture, then stir in sour cream.
Beat well.
Add flavorings and turn into pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours or longer if needed.
Test doneness with toothpick.
Cool for 10 minutes and turn out of pan.
Freezes well.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, granulated sugar, 1/4 cup melted margarine, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Place in well-greased casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour together.
Cut in margarine.
Add nuts in and combine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy bake cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar, cheese, juice, salt and vanilla.
Begin to blend, then beat eggs in one at a time.
Pour mixture into crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the center levels with the edges.
Chill before serving.

title: bohemian kolaches(buns)
directions: Scald milk; cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream butter, sugar, salt and egg yolk together with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add yeast, milk and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat mixer at medium speed 5 minutes, scrape.
Batter should be smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour, a little at a time, to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of bowl.
Place in greased bowl, turn dough over to grease top.
Cover, let rise until doubled, about 2 hours. Stir down; turn onto lightly floured board and divide into 24 balls.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Press each piece to make a hole in center for filling.
Fill each hollow with 1 level tablespoonful filling. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 24 Kolaches (buns).

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop rounded tablespoonful of dough about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheets before transferring to storage.

title: orange-mint julep
directions: Place fresh mint leaves in a pan.
Cover with 2 1/2 cups water; bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
When cool, add sugar, lemon juice and orange juice.
Heat the mixture, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Store in the refrigerator in a covered container.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate pie
