directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Whip in Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal marble squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg. Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle semi-sweet chocolate chips over top.
Place in oven for 3 minutes.
Run knife through to marbleize.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool; cut.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: okra pickle
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to boil.
Add dill seed if desired. Pack okra into jars which have been sterilized and pour boiling vinegar solution over okra and seal.
Let set in cool place for a month or more before using.

title: baked apples
directions: Quarter or slice apples; take core out.
Put butter, sugar and vanilla flavoring in apples.
Bake until done.

title: no name pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Brown pecans and coconut in melted margarine in a 300° oven for about 15 minutes.
If you choose to use pecans only, and no coconut, use 1/4 stick margarine.
Layer into baked pie crust the following:	1/3 of the cream cheese mixture; 1/3 of the butterscotch topping (drizzled over the cream cheese), and 1/3 of the nuts mixture, Repeat layers and freeze.

title: broccoli-cauliflower-pea salad
directions: Soak broccoli and cauliflower in salt water for 8-10 minutes. Drain.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Mix salad dressing, mayonnaise, and sour cream.
Toss with vegetables and refrigerate.

title: paula's banana bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs, milk and bananas together.
Then add salt, flour, soda and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in floured bread pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (time may vary).

title: tomatoes and noodles
directions: Cook macaroni according to instructions on bag.
Fry bacon and chopped onion until crispy.
Add bacon and onion to macaroni.
Add 2 cans of tomato soup and one can water.
Season to taste.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Dip round steak in flour.
Brown in oil with onions and celery.
Drain and put in crock-pot.
Add cream of mushroom soup, beef bouillon and water.
Stir gently until mixed well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
This will thicken as cooks.
Turn on low for longer cooking time or high for faster.
Serve over rice.
Double for larger meal.
Great cooked Saturday for Sunday dinner.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Pour turkey drippings from roasting pan into 4-cup measure. Remove 1/4 cup fat from drippings.
Place in saucepan.
Skim off and discard remaining fat from drippings.
Add broth to drippings to make 4 cups.
Blend flour into fat until smooth, then gradually add drippings.
Cook and stir until gravy comes to a boil and thickens over medium heat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add giblets.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: figgy bars(makes about 2 dozen squares)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a small bowl, blend all ingredients well.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar in saucepan.
Add mustard and butter.
Beat in eggs until smooth.
Stir in vinegar and water. Remove from heat as soon as it boils.
Cool, then stir in mayonnaise.
Add pickles, hard-boiled eggs, etc.
This recipe covers 2 quarts cooked potatoes or 2 cups uncooked macaroni.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Mash the unpeeled potatoes with your hands (don't mash too much).
Add the rest of the ingredients except for the reserved bacon fat, and toss gently to mix.

title: corn soup
directions: Grate or chop corn.
Add boiling water and onion. Cook 15 minutes.
Strain.
Melt butter and stir in flour. Blend.
Add stock and seasonings. Cook, stirring constantly 5 minutes. Stir in strained corn pulp and cook 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with mixer, adding enough orange juice to reach desired consistency.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix the Worcestershire sauce and the soy together.
Sprinkle the garlic and lemon pepper before throwing them on the grill.

title: corn salsa
directions: Place pepper directly over gas flame until blackened and blistered all over.
Cool.
Peel.
Chop coarsely.
In food processor combine pepper, corn, jalapeno and garlic.
Process until finely chopped.
Add cilantro, chives, vinegar and salt.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bettye's creeping crust cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix the flour, 1 cup of sugar, baking powder and sweet milk.
Spoon over melted butter.
Heat fruit and 1 cup of sugar and pour over dough.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and boiling water.
Stir until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Cook over low heat until soft ball stage. Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and pour into buttered pan.
Cool and cot in squares.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; pour into a Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tostados
directions: On tostado shell, spread sour cream, chicken, lettuce, onion and tomato in that order.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refried beans can be added, if desired.

title: chicken and garden vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to medium.
Cook uncovered for 7 to 10 minutes or until pasta is tender and vegetables are crisp-tender.
Makes 6 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer onion, bell pepper and potatoes over meat.
Mix celery soup and sour cream and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours.
This is ideal to put in oven and bake while you're at church.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will need a pan with sides or an ovenproof dish.
Spray dish with Pam.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and Italian dressing.
Cook at 350° until chicken is done.
Good on the grill too.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Precook broccoli.
Saute onion in butter.
Add salt.
Slightly beat eggs, adding cottage cheese, green onions, broccoli and cornbread mix.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add mixture.
Bake approximately 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: six week muffins
directions: Add sugar to warm melted shortening.
Beat in eggs.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and milk in large bowl.
Heat oven to 350° and melt butter in pan.
Pour batter in pan and cover with fruit.
Bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: double chocolate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, beat margarine, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually add flour mixture, stir in chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: marinade for barbecue chicken
directions: Marinate for at least 2 hours before barbecuing.
This same marinade can be used for ribs.
This will "do" 1 fryer.
Add more for more chicken.

title: chicken soup
directions: Add chicken meat back to broth.
Add Veg-All.
Mix flour with water and add to broth.
Add bouillon cubes and seasoning.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
Add soup.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of large bread pan.
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.
Bake 1 hour or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Place the first 9 ingredients in a large soup pot and simmer until vegetables are tender.
While soup is simmering, make tiny meatballs to taste.
Brown, then drain.
Add kidney beans to soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Add meatballs to soup; simmer 10 minutes. Add elbow macaroni and simmer until tender.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Mix cheese with bacon bits, mushrooms, onion and peas.
Layer spinach with cheese mixture.
Mix sour cream, mayo and sugar. Pour this mixture on top of spinach, then add more grated cheese. Cover well and refrigerate.
Leave overnight.

title: easy egg rolls
directions: Starting with cabbage, place ingredients alternately in electric skillet, adding sausage last, and cook until cabbage is transparent.
Wrap in egg roll wraps.
(Secure wraps by putting egg white on the last closing of wrap.) Deep fry until golden brown.

title: fruit punch
directions: All frozen drinks are undiluted.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Let rise about 5 minutes.
Roll out, cut and bake in hot oven (425°) until brown.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add rest, adding enough broth to make real soggy.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip #3
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook over low heat until process cheese spread melts.
Serve hot with green pepper strips, carrot and celery sticks, chips or French bread tubes, if desired.
Makes 3 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: You can either cook the vegetables in the microwave or by the boiling method.
Drain after cooked.
Put vegetables in the casserole.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Then spread with Cheddar cheese soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
During the last 10 minutes of baking, add French onions on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain ground meat.
Add taco mix envelope according to directions on package.

title: easy hamburg casserole
directions: Put hamburg in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer the potatoes on top of meat, then add onions, green peppers and carrots.
Put tomatoes and seasonings in next. Last, top with shredded cheese.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: deli pickles
directions: Fill 1-gallon size jar with cucumber spears, dill, garlic and pepper.
Boil water, vinegar, salt, sugar and bay leaves for 3 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cover cucumbers with brine; seal and refrigerate overnight.
Can be stored in refrigerator without having to seal in boiling water (canning jars).

title: "quick" chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into cubes and cook in small amount of water.
Add 2 cups (or cans) of chicken broth and cream of chicken soup plus 1 can milk.
Stir with whip to mix.
Taste.
Add granulated chicken bouillon as desired to taste.
Cut up 20 tortillas into small bite size pieces.
Add to mixture.
Heat mixture 30 to 60 minutes, until "dumplings" puff up.
(Do not boil mixture at any point.) Excellent for crock-pot cooking also.
However, don't put tortillas in until the last hour of cooking.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to other.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Also makes 24 cupcakes.

title: easy baked potatoes
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Arrange in single layer with onion chunks tucked in between.
Melt butter with garlic.
Remove garlic.
Drizzle butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and celery seed.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl with your hands.
May need to add water to help ingredients stick together.
Roll into medium sized balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes around 40 balls.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll rolls onto cookie sheet, bake approximately 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix dressing and cream cheese; spread on baked roll.
Add vegetables and top with Parmesan cheese (follow oven temperature on package of rolls).

title: honey drops
directions: Combine powdered milk and crumbs.
Add honey.
Mix.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
May be dipped in chocolate or rolled in coconut.
Variations:
Add 1 cup chocolate chips or raisins to the honey mixture.

title: poor man's fruitcake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix and knead until dough is stiff.
Divide dough into 4 sections. Roll each section until fairly thin.
Cut and place into cake pans.
Bake each layer about 15 minutes at 450°.
Layer each layer with apple mixture (cooked with sugar and spices).
Stack layers as you put apples on.

title: croquettes
directions: Grind or chip the material and combine with the white sauce and seasonings.
Allow to cool and stiffen.
Shape into balls, cones or rolls, allowing 1 tablespoon for each croquette.
Roll in crumbs, then dip in egg, slightly beaten and mixed with cold water.
Roll in crumbs again.
Fry in deep fat at 375° to 380° until delicately brown (about 1 minute).
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Place in casserole.
Add pineapple, brown sugar and margarine.
Add dash of cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Top with marshmallows.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Return to oven until marshmallows are toasted.

title: golden corn sticks
directions: Stir thoroughly the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine egg, sour cream and oil.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until blended.
Preheat corn stick pans; grease generously.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, milk and egg.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to milk mixture.
Beat all together.
Add walnuts. Let stand in loaf pan at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onion in butter.
Add all but last two ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour or so.
Mix flour into sour cream. Just before serving, mix with beef mixture.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: overnight eggs
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cut crust from 8 slices of bread. Put in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Place 8 more slices of crustless bread on top.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread.
Crush corn flakes; mix in melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of bread.
Cover with foil and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: sour cream casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, soup, sour cream, butter, onion and cheese; pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Refrigerate, covered, 8 hours or overnight.
Before baking, bring to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top potatoes with cornflake crumbs during last 20 minutes of baking.

title: festive florentine crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix broccoli, cheese, bread crumbs and bacon in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted. Unroll dough.
Separate into 16 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise.
Spread each with rounded teaspoonful of mixture. Roll up, starting at wide end.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Brush each roll with beaten egg.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: bethel's peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let set until slightly congealed.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Let chill until set.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal and boiling water.
Stir in shortening until melted.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix well. Stir together remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to cereal mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps up to 4 weeks.

title: pickled beets
directions: Heat vinegar, water, sugar and salt to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add beets; simmer another 5 minutes.
Place in container all ingredients.
Chill for 4 hours or overnight.

title: sandi's coleslaw
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Cream in eggs and vanilla extract.
Mix in oats and flour (in which you've
combined baking soda and salt).
Mix in pecans and chocolate chips.
Ball out the batter in about golf ball size balls.
Place on air-cushion cookie sheets, then half-flatten with fork.
Bake in preheated oven of 375° until just done in center and just browning on edges, about 15 minutes, check often.

title: arkansas chocolate gravy
directions: Cook ingredients over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Place 1/2 tablespoon of margarine on your plate and pour gravy over it, stirring until margarine melts.
This gravy is a breakfast treat.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: grape jelly
directions: Wash and cook grapes.
Bring grapes to boil, continue to cook until all grapes have popped (about 20 minutes).
Strain juice.
In a large pot (5-quart), bring juice to rapid boil and add sugar. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 12 to 15 minutes on medium heat.
Pour into hot, sterilized jelly jars.
Seal.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Dissolve soda in applesauce.
Mix spices with flavoring.
Add raisins, dates and nuts.
Add sugar mixture to applesauce, mixing well, and add flavoring to which nuts and fruits have been added.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in well-greased and floured tube pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter by hand in large bowl.
Gradually add milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour in crusts and freeze.
When frozen, wrap tightly.
Do not thaw to serve.

title: smothered dogs(kids dish)
directions: Cook noodles, then slice one side open.
Place hot dog inside and smother with chili, roll and put in 11 x 13-inch pan.
After all have been placed in pan, cover with remaining chili and smooth cheese over entire top.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Serve with salad.

title: baked trout
directions: Spray foil with Pam.
Place fish on foil; add seasonings. Close foil tightly.
Bake at 350° (preheated oven) for 30 minutes. Open foil; broil for a few minutes.
Great over charcoal. Cooking times vary on thickness of fish.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Add walnuts and mix with a wooden spoon.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Drop batter by teaspoonful onto paper, 2 1/2-inches apart.
Decorate each with small amount of pistachios. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and oil with the sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Measure flour, cream of tartar and soda into sifter. Add to other ingredients.
Chill dough.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 13 minutes or until lightly brown around edges. Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar and salt; heat and let cool. Add remaining ingredients, except cabbage.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook hen until tender (I pressure mine).
Crumble breads in very large mixing bowl.
Add hot water and keep mixing until bread is not too lumpy.
Add enough hot water to start thinning.
Add small amount of hot broth.
Add rest of ingredients and finish with broth.
Should be almost soupy.
Pour half in deep baking pan.
Add chicken (I take mine off bone).
Cover with rest of dressing.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 350° oven until light brown.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, melted butter and milk.
Mix pineapple with bread.
Pour eggs, sugar and butter over bread and pineapple. Cook at 350° until golden brown.
Great with ham.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix together well.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.
This is good mixed ahead of time and baked later or the day before.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into 1/4-inch slices.
Soak overnight in lime and 1 gallon water.
Next day, drain and soak 4 hours in clear water; remove the centers.

title: chocolate chip cookie recipe
directions: Cream margarine, then add sugar, eggs and dry ingredients. Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: crumb topped broccoli cheese casserole(there's never a crumb left!)
directions: Prepare and cook carrots.
Cut into lengthwise strips or medallions.
In large skillet, cook and stir brown sugar, salt, orange peel and butter until bubbly.
Add carrots and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally (about 10 minutes), or until carrots are glazed and heated through.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into a large skillet and brown evenly; drain.
Stir eggs, cornmeal, cream-style corn, milk and vegetable oil together.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix above ingredients except Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip and fold in good.
Chill and serve.

title: corn relish
directions: In Dutch oven, mix sugar, flour, salt, mustard, turmeric and corn; stir in vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Add vegetables and simmer, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Pack into canning jars, wipe rims and seal and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and pour off grease, then add tomatoes, minced garlic, oregano, parsley, salt and water.
Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on box. Drain noodles and layer in pan:
noodles first, then meat mixture and cheeses (Parmesan, Mozzarella and Cheddar).
Make in three layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil and add 3 tea bags.
Serve hot.

title: wild game steaks (deer)
directions: Take
loin and strip all membranes from it.
Marinate in red wine,
garlic
powder
and
package
of Swiss steak for 45 minutes.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Fry for 3 minutes to each side.

title: peppermint tea
directions: Heat water over stove or in the microwave.
Add tea bag and let set for 5 minutes, then add the candy cane.
Stir until candy cane is melted and then reheat.

title: betty's special coffee cake
directions: Add remaining batter on top, then finish with last of cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° in a tube pan for 60 minutes or 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken breasts skin side up in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with rice. Boneless, skinless chicken breasts are fine also.

title: butterhorns
directions: Cut margarine into flour in bowl with pastry blender until crumbly.
Add mixture of egg yolk and sour cream; mix well.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Roll dough into 3 circles.
Cut each into 16 wedges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, pecans and half the egg white in bowl; mix well.
Spoon onto wedges.
Roll up from wide end.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
48 servings.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Add eggs, milk and melted margarine to dry ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Pour batter on hot crepe skillet.
Tilt to spread to shape and cook 1 minute and flip.
Serve with sugar, whipping cream, fresh fruit or just butter and cinnamon sugar.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom and sausage casserole
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch dish put bread cubes, then sausage, mushrooms and cheese.
In bowl mix eggs, milk and dry mustard and pour over casserole; refrigerate overnight.
In morning bring to room temperature.
Mix milk and soup; pour over casserole.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 75 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
In a large skillet, cook onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in margarine or butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, parsley, salt, paprika, red pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: caponata
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a skillet and fry eggplant until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Heat remaining oil in a heavy pan; add onion.
Gently saute for 15 minutes.
Add celery, olives, tomatoes, pinch of salt and pepper, sugar, vinegar, capers and eggplant.
Cook for 10 minutes until vinegar has evaporated. Remove from heat and let cool.
Chill; serve cold.

title: baby wipes
directions: Here is a great way to recycle old crayons.
You need the following items:

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into a flat pan.
Sprinkle the Pepperidge Farm dressing on top.
Pour the melted butter or oleo on top; heat for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: quick and easy dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast in water. Add sugar, oil, egg and flour. Mix until well blended. Refrigerate. Needs to set at least 1 hour (may set longer). When ready to bake, drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tins. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon glazed persimmon bars
directions: Mix and set aside persimmon and baking soda.
Combine and mix with previous mixture the egg, sugar, salad oil and raisins. Combine and blend with previous mixture the cinnamon, nutmeg, flour, salt, cloves and nuts.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool for 5 minutes and glaze.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter and mix flour and corn in baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Stir once every 15 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Microwave cheese for 20 seconds to soften.
In a
bowl, mix cheese and mayonnaise.
Cut Italian bread lengthwise and spread cheese mixture on both sides.
Put bread on a cookie sheet and place under broiler for 2 minutes or until cheese begins to bubble.
Do not brown.

title: butter-fried parsnip
directions: In covered 3-quart saucepan, boil parsnips in water until tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Dip parsnips in 1/4 cup melted butter.
In plastic bag combine flour and seasoned salt.
Add parsnips; shake to coat with flour mixture.
In 10-inch skillet melt 1/4 cup butter until sizzling.
Add parsnips.
Cook over medium high heat, turning occasionally until all sides are golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Layer pork chops in casserole dish; make layer of tomato and layer of onion.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over onion, tomato and pork chops.
Pour cream of mushroom soup and water into dish. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Measure flour; add Crisco and salt.
Crumble.
Put egg in a 1 cup measuring cup; stir.
Add vinegar and water to top of cup. Blend with flour and Crisco.
Make dough.
Stores well in the refrigerator or freezer.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onion in a frying pan.
Pour off grease and cool on a paper towel-covered plate or cookie sheet.
Tear lettuce into bite sized pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a humongous bowl (we use a punch bowl).
Last, add salad dressing and chips.
Toss well.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add all dry ingredients together; mix well.
Mix egg, milk, oil and brown sugar together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix. Spoon 1/3 full into muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Add flour and remaining eggs alternately.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add flour, apples and pecans; blend.
Place in greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Do not open oven door until done.

title: 7 layer taco salad
directions: In large flat dish, 8 x 12-inch, arrange ingredients in layers.
Cover with grated Longhorn cheese.
Top with medium size package crushed Fritos.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Put sausage into bottom of dish and add eggs.
Top with cheese; then top with rolls.
(Can be put together the night before and refrigerated.)
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown meat in a skillet, pour off fat.
Remove pan from heat and stir in soup, sour cream, chili powder, salt and pepper.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Measure all into large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping side and bottom of bowl constantly.
Pour into pan or pans.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: tony the tiger candy
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cereal and drop on wax paper.

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Place cream cheese in small bowl of electric mixer.
Beat until creamy.

title: fudge
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot water with the oleo.
Stir in the sugar.
Add the Karo, coffee cream or half and half and salt. Cook until 240°, or until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add the butter and vanilla.
Cool until bottom of pan is warm.
Beat with electric mixer until it holds its shape when dropped from spoon.
Add the toasted pecans.
Drop onto wax paper.
Store in tins when cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes 45 minutes.
Peel and slice.
Slice onion. Dissolve bouillon cube; add vinegar, oil, black pepper and paprika.
Pour over hot potatoes and onion.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix with peanut butter, oil, water and eggs.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Before baking, dip a fork in water, then press the top of each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies each.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald milk and cocoa; stir well.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to eggs.
Pour small amount of chocolate mixture over egg mixture, stirring vigorously.
Return to double boiler; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Put into baked pie shell and cover with meringue or whipped cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: quickie hot dog and sauerkraut lunch
directions: Cut about 12 inches of plastic wrap and arrange some sauerkraut as a bottom layer.
Cut up 1 or 2 hot dogs and place on top.
Pour some Heinz chili sauce and cover with additional kraut. Seal edges of plastic wrap and microwave for 3 minutes.
Use aluminum foil and put on your barbecue grill.

title: pork tenderloin with onion-apple cream
directions: Place pork on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
In a small bowl, stir together whipping cream, sherry, mustard and horseradish.
Brush half of mixture over pork.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven, brushing often with cream mixture, for 45 to 60 minutes or until pork meat in center is not longer pink when slashed.

title: strawberry jello deluxe
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Cool and add strawberries and other fruit.
Put half of mixture in refrigerator to get firm. Then spread with sour cream and add rest of Jell-O mixture. Refrigerate.

title: apple dumplings(makes 10 servings.  prep time:  20 minutes.)
directions: Roll out biscuits and spoon pie filling into each one, closing top by pulling top together and pinching edges.
Put in a 9 x 12 baking dish.

title: pizza noodle bake
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put a layer of uncooked noodles in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add beef and onion.
Mix tomato sauce, water and spices together and pour over meat and noodles.
Bake at 350° for one hour (covered).
During the last 7 minutes, top the dish with cheese and finish baking covered.
Cut into squares and serve at once.
Serves 4.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over 1 pound mushrooms (fresh).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: one pan potatoes and chicken
directions: In a large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil, about 5 minutes on high. Add potatoes. Saute and toss until potatoes are light brown. Add barbecue sauce and tarragon.
Toss until heated through.

title: hot ham 'n cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix together margarine, mustard and onions.
Spread on both halves of buns.
Layer the ham and cheese on the bottom half of the bun.
Top with top half of bun.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese. Beat until smooth. Stir in balance of ingredients and chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on 1 large pizza pan or 2 small pans. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken, reserving broth.
Mix soups, milk and black pepper together.
Melt oleo in 1 1/2 cups of the chicken broth. Add stuffing.
Mix together.
In a large casserole dish, place the chicken.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Spoon on stuffing and broth mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients; add water and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in salad dressing.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Use a 6-quart Dutch oven for this recipe.
About an hour and 15 minutes before serving, heat to the boiling point over high heat all the ingredients except the heavy cream.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Coarsely mash potatoes with potato masher or slotted spoon.
Add heavy cream, stir and serve.
Makes 9 one cup servings.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli 8 minutes on full power (4 minutes per package).
Melt butter; add chopped onion.
Cook 2 minutes and 30 seconds on full power until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cook in oven for 10 minutes on full power.

title: "the pantry's" blueberry muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, salt, baking powder, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Divide dough evenly into 12 greased muffin cups or cupcake cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top of each before putting into oven.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Prepare peppers for stuffing. Brown ground beef with onion in heavy skillet.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper while frying. Drain well. Mix in rice.
Loosely stuff each pepper with meat and rice mixture.
Stand upright in deep saucepan so they touch and support each other. Pour sauce so it surrounds peppers, but does not cover them.
Cover and simmer slowly about 1 hour or until tender.
Use sauce to pour over peppers when served.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil thoroughly to mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and beat.
Fold in diced apples and chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish, greased and floured.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and dust with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: aloha punch
directions: Do not dilute the frozen orange juice.
If necessary, add more lemonade and 7-Up.
If you need more, you may add 3 or more 7-Ups.

title: yeast bread or rolls
directions: Add the yeast and water mixture to remaining ingredients.
Add flour last and mix with a wooden spoon (mix well).
Place in a large bowl that has been greased well.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator several hours before using.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup warm water; let cool.
Mix oil with cake mix and beat.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each egg. Add strawberries and beat.
Frost with white frosting with crushed strawberries in it.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in bowl.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour 9 x 14-inch glass dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar or chocolate frosting.

title: seven layer microwave bars
directions: Place butter in 9-inch square baking dish.
Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 minutes, or until butter melts.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and sugar; mix well.
Press mixture firmly against bottom of dish.
Microwave at High for 2 minutes, rotating dish once.
Layer coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and pecans over crust.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over pecans.
Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave for 10 to 18 minutes, or just until bubbly around edges.
Cool completely; cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Melt butter and mix with potatoes.
Add soup, sour cream, onions, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Mix 2 cups corn flakes with 1/2 cup melted butter and spread over top of potato mixture.
Cook in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: miracle chicken
directions: Layer ham and cheese over chicken.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes (until chicken is done) at 350°.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in a greased baking dish.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Melt butter and rub in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; add cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add other ingredients and mix well. Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sasha's favorite meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Apricot Barbecue Sauce.
Form into walnut-sized balls.
Pour Apricot Barbecue Sauce over meatballs in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry souffle
directions: Mix pecans, flour, sugar and butter to make crumb mixture. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring often. Remove from oven and let cool. Remove 1/3 of crumbs and reserve for topping. Spread remaining crumbs evenly over bottom of pan. Beat egg whites until peaks form. Slowly add sugar and beat 5 more minutes. Fold in lemon juice and drained strawberries. Fold in whipped topping. Spread mixture over crumbs. Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top. Cover and freeze for at least 6 hours. Remove and let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before serving. Garnish with a fresh strawberry with the stem.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Stir in pizza sauce, undrained mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Combine macaroni and milk.

title: light and crunchy spinach salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients in a large serving bowl. Toss with vinaigrette just before serving. Serves 4.

title: lemony punch
directions: In pitcher, combine grape juice, sugar and lemon juice concentrate.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add club soda and serve over ice.
Serves about 7.

title: never fail meringue pie topping
directions: In saucepan, blend cornstarch with cold water.
Add to boiling water.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.

title: roast beef and swiss rolls
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion powder and poppy seed in small bowl.
Spread butter mixture inside each roll.
Top with 1 slice beef and 1 slice cheese in each roll.
Cover with other half roll. Wrap each sandwich in paper towel or napkin.
Place in microwave 2 at a time.
Microwave on High until cheese melts.

title: barbecue cajun shrimp
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add garlic, Cajun seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp and cook just until shrimp are pink and firm to touch.
Add stock and white wine and heat just to boiling point, scraping bits from the sides of the pan. Serve on heated platter with warm sourdough bread.
Great with rice.

title: dreamy apricot salad(big)
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and water in small saucepan and bring to boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and Jell-O.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit.
Set aside and cool.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Stir in Jell-O mixture and nuts.
Pour into bowl and chill until firm.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, whipping cream and flour.
Cut up butter and add to corn.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Cook pudding with the 3 cups of milk and set aside; cool.
Mix together flour, butter and granulated sugar.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on top of cooled crust.
Spread cooled pudding on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: texas style shrimp and cornbread
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until onion is tender; stir in cornstarch and salt.
Fold in tomato wedges, catsup and hot pepper sauce.
Cook over low heat until sauce is thickened, stirring frequently.
Add shrimp and heat thoroughly.
To serve, spoon shrimp sauce over cornbread.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl combine the first four ingredients.
Pour sugar over and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: marinade for chuck steak or roasts
directions: Marinate chuck steak or roast overnight at least 6 hours, turning so both sides have been in marinade.
If roasting in oven, remove from marinade but baste every once in a while with the marinade.
If using an out-door grill, turn over 10 minutes and baste with the marinade until done as you like it.

title: bulgur pilaf(cracked wheat)
directions: Coat medium pan with oil and melt butter.
If using onion, saute 2 minutes.
Add noodles and saute until golden color.
Add bulgur and water or broth.
Water or broth must be boiling hot before using.
Add salt and pepper.
If using currants, add along with bulgur.
Bring to boil and lower to simmer for 10 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Sprinkle with pine nuts before serving. Makes 4 servings, 1 cup each.
Bulgur is a very nutritious food. It is a good meat substitute if served with beans to make complete protein.

title: easy chile rellanos
directions: Remove seeds from chiles; rinse, drain and pat dry.
Place a strip of Jack cheese on each chile and fold chile over cheese. Beat eggs and gradually add flour, beating until smooth.
Add milk, pepper and Tabasco.
Beat thoroughly.
Arrange 1/2 of the stuffed chiles in a well-greased 7 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the chiles with 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Repeat layer.
Pour the egg mixture over the top.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom and up the sides of pie plate; then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of cream cheese.
Heat chilli and beans in microwave or top of stove.
Mix taco sauce with chilli and beans and spread over cheese layers.
Cover top with shredded Cheddar cheese, melt until bubbly.
Can heat in microwave or convection oven.
If heated in oven, heat at 350°.
Eat with nacho chips.

title: cold or vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll the crescent rolls and lay flat on a cookie sheet. Bake as directed and cool.

title: red beet jelly(old fashioned rex jelly recipe)
directions: First peel 6 to 8 beets and cook until tender with enough water to cover to make 6 cups of juice.
When beets are done, strain through cloth, to have clear juice.

title: pastor al's wuffins(cross between waffles and muffins)
directions: Place into blender 1 cup distilled water, almonds or cashews, dates, vanilla or almond flavoring.
Blend until everything is pureed.
Add this to the rolled oats, millet or barley flour, salt and whole wheat flour.
Add the 3 to 4 cups of water and stir well.
Spray waffle iron with Pam.
Pour 1 cup batter, being certain to go all the way to edges of iron.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes according to iron.

title: vegetable cheese tart
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until blended. Spoon into pie or tart shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: mike's hush puppies
directions: Mix meal, flour, egg, onion and buttermilk until soupy.
Use tablespoon to dip mix and put in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Slash onion and garlic several times and let stay in dressing until all is used.

title: sunshine fruit dip
directions: In medium
bowl, stir together all ingredients except fruit. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit. This fruit dip can be a light refreshing dessert too!

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: In food processor, process until fluffy the cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 c. sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Spread mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over cheese mixture.
Beat remaining 3 eggs until foamy.
Do not over beat.
Add corn syrup, the remaining 1/4 c. sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla and salt.
Mix well and pour this over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into 9-inch by 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until hot and bubbly.

title: 7 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl and chill.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, corn syrup, water, egg whites, cream of tartar and salt.
Cook over boiling water, beating with mixer until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Continue beating until frosting holds deep swirls.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Cut tenderized steak into serving sizes.
Place steak in a roaster.
Pour sauce over the steak.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
(This sauce is also excellent over your favorite meatball recipe.)

title: soft michigan rock cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumber, onion and garlic in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with ice cubes.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients except liquid artificial sweetener in a 4-quart pan; add cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and boil gently for two minutes.
Stir in liquid artificial sweetener. Remove garlic clove.
Spoon into sterile jars.
Seal.
Yield:
5 cups.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 1 g, fat 0 g, calories 28.
One serving = 1/2 vegetable exchange.

title: spicy shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until shrimp turns pink. Remove and allow to cool, then chill.
Drain off liquids.
Serve with lemon slices and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: judy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and mix well.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheets until done.

title: squash rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Mix baking mix and squash.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into 12 inch circle.
Spread with margarine. Cut into 12 wedges.
Roll up, beginning at round edge.
Place rolls with points underneath about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
About 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 12 rolls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Scoop out warm potatoes from skin and mix with seasonings. Beat until smooth.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks and cream to potato mixture; blend well.
Stiffly beat egg whites and fold into the potato mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about an hour until center is set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger.
Add taco seasoning; mix.
Add all other ingredients, except taco chips and Western dressing, which you add just before serving.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except chives.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with chives.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well. Combine cream cheese and onion in bowl.
Mix well.
Add milk and mix until smooth.
Mix in spinach.
Spoon into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix thoroughly with crumbs.
Press evenly over bottom and sides of pie plate; cool.

title: edie's brownies
directions: Sift together into bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cocoa and dry milk.
Add all at once the oil, water, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Beat hard for 1 minute.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread batter in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake pulls from sides of pan.
Do not overbake.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and dip each piece chicken in sauce. Place chicken in dish and baste while cooking.
Cover while baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and sour cream.
Whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit. Chill until ready to use.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together and freeze in a 13 x 9-inch container.
Thaw just slightly enough to cut, before serving.

title: college style pasta
directions: Boil pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in a colander.
Put the pasta in a bowl and add the tuna and vegetables.
Mix and pour in dressing to your own taste.
I also use Italian instead of Ranch or canned chicken instead of tuna. Makes enough for 2 people or two meals.

title: microwave beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter in a large microwavable bowl for 2 minutes on High.
Boil water and add the bouillon cubes, set aside.
Cut sirloin into strips.
Place in plastic bag.
Add flour, shake and coat meat.
Add coated meat to onion and garlic. Add bouillon.
Add catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Mix. Microwave 8 minutes on Medium-high; mix.
Microwave another 8 minutes on Medium-high.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Add sour cream to top, if desired.
Easy, quick and delicious.

title: malaysian vegetable dish
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in water with a small amount of oil.
Bring to boil.
Turn off heat.
Fry onion, carrots and meat in oil; reduce to low heat until cooked.
Do not overcook.
It is better crispy.
If desired, add mushrooms and water chestnuts. Mix everything together.
Add seasoning as desired.
Serve and enjoy!
Serves 6 plus depending on the amount of vegetables you prepare.
If you use meat, cut it in tiny pieces.
We preferred it without meat.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Place 4 scoops, 1/2 cup of ice cream in pan and freeze until firm.
In a mixing bowl, stir egg and vanilla.
In a shallow dish, mix flakes and cinnamon.
Dip each frozen ice cream ball in egg mixture and roll in cereal.
Re-freeze until firm.
In bowl mix other egg and vanilla.
Re-dip refrozen ice cream balls in this and roll them again in cereal.
Freeze again until firm, about 1 hour.
Heat oil to 375° and fry 2 ice cream balls until golden brown, 15 seconds.
Drain.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain the green beans, combine with the soup, pepper and 1/2 can of the onions.
Pour the mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Yields 4 servings.

title: spanish bread
directions: Mix flour, white sugar, salt, brown sugar, oil and cinnamon like pie crust.
Take out 1/2 cup crumbs for top and add 1/2 cup chopped nuts to topping; set aside.
To mixture, add soda, baking powder, egg and buttermilk.
Beat 4 minutes with mixer.
Grease 2 small pans; sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Remove from pans after cooled.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli using package directions or if using fresh broccoli, peel, cut and steam approximately 8 to 10 minutes, until tender, but firm.
Drain.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in a little butter.
Mix all ingredients and pour in a large baking dish (or 2 small dishes).
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm. Roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Poke holes in warm cake.
Pour milk and cream of coconut over warm cake.
Let chill; top with Cool Whip and shredded coconut.

title: walla walla asparagus
directions: Slice eggs and olives.
Assemble in layers in an ovenproof casserole dish in this order:

Thin layer soda cracker crumbs, asparagus, sliced eggs to cover asparagus, layer of one type of cheese, olives, 1/2 of one can of mushroom soup spread over layer, thin layer of soda cracker crumbs, mushrooms, asparagus, sliced eggs, layer of second type of cheese, olives, layer of soda cracker crumbs and top with soup to cover thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for one hour, uncovered.

title: dilled vegetable-barley soup
directions: Place barley and water in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes, or until tender.
In a soup kettle or saucepan, saute onion, salt and bay leaf in butter until onion is soft.
Add carrot and celery; cook over medium heat 5 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients and barley.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Preparation time:
2 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple coconut and strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Boil pineapple and sugar and let cool.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake with fork and cover with pineapple mixture. Mix pudding according to package directions and pour over pineapple layer.
Slice bananas and lay on top and cover with Cool Whip, then coconut, then strawberries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across the grain into bite-sized strips.
In a small bowl, stir together sour cream, flour and tomato paste.
Stir in water, bouillon granules and pepper. Set aside.
Cook the fettuccine according to package directions, omitting the cooking oil and salt.
Drain well.

title: wiki wiki roast chicken
directions: Salt
chicken inside and out.
Place in
a
foil
lined pan; let stand for 1 hour.
Rub chicken with
shoyu or oyster sauce. Place in oven.
Bake at 475° (that's
right, 475°) for 45 minutes.
You can make a nice gravy
with
the
drippings. This is a fast dish when you're in a hurry.

title: macaroni-fish loaf
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Combine parsley, onion, soup, sauce, salt and eggs.
Pour over macaroni and fish.
Place olives in bottom of greased 10 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Cover with grated cheese.
Carefully put macaroni mixture into pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Unmold; garnish as desired.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan and saut meat and onion until brown.
Add soup and corn.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in greased baking dish. Cover with potatoes.
Brush top with egg yolk.
Bake in 450° oven until brown.

title: icebox pudding
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Add milk and water. Cook until slightly thickened (5 to 10 minutes), constantly stirring.
Alternate chocolate and wafers.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F and place wings in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Combine all ingredients together and mix well. Brush generously over wings.
Bake about 25 minutes, basting frequently.
Serve wings with Plum Dipping Sauce.

title: gourmet peas
directions: Cook peas as directed; drain.
Add mayonnaise to moisten. Stir in crumbled bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and saute with onion.
Add soup and milk; cut cheese into small pieces.
Add to mixture and melt.
Add broccoli. Heat and eat.

title: orange surprise
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple and blot.
Cut pineapple chunks into halves.
Mix with rest of ingredients.

title: spicy crab spread
directions: In a large bowl, combine crabmeat, cheese, mayonnaise, green pepper, onions, garlic powder, salt, dry mustard and red pepper; stir until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Serve chilled with French bread or crackers. Yield: About 3 cups spread.

title: annie's pecan pies
directions: Put 1 cup pecans in bottom of each pie shell. Mix all other ingredients well and pour over pecans. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 325° oven.

title: beef chinese casserole(for those who love chinese food, this is a good recipe to try.)
directions: Cook hamburger and drain, except for 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Put in casserole dish and add the remaining ingredients, except for the chow mein noodles.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Take out and sprinkle chow mein noodles on top. Bake an additional 10 minutes, then serve.
Serves 6.

title: roast beef
directions: Wash roast.
Salt and pepper and put in a pan.
Add the 2 cans of soup.
In a bowl mix a quart of water, brown gravy and Lipton onion-mushroom soup mix; add to roast.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or until done.
Serve gravy over cream potatoes or rice.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Prepare peaches and place in bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent browning.
Stir; turn fruit into a 3-quart baking dish. Combine cornstarch and 1 cup sugar; stir to mix well.
Sprinkle mixture over fruit in baking dish and stir until well combined. Taste and add additional sugar if needed.
Dot prepared peach mixture with 2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside while preparing biscuit topping.

title: gram's mashed potato rolls
directions: Mix in bowl, knead very little and let rise to twice it's size.
Shape, place in greased pan(s) and let rise again.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 20 minutes.

title: java cream tarts
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in top of a double boiler.
Add coffee and milk; mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour slowly over beaten eggs.
Mix well and return to double boiler and cook over boiling water for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool.
Pour into tart shells and chill thoroughly.
Makes 8 tarts.

title: lo-cal lemon pie
directions: In a blender, combine hot water and Jell-O until well blended. Add 1 cup cottage cheese and blend.
Add lemon juice and blend. Add remaining cottage cheese and blend well.
Pour into a bowl. Stir in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. You may substitute lime Jell-O and lime juice.

title: homemade ice cream with oreo cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in milk, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Pour into aluminum 9x5-inch loaf pan, foil lined.
Cover and freeze for 6 hours.

title: bit-o-brie
directions: Mix Kahlua, brown sugar and pecans.
Stir well. Remove top rind from Brie. Discard rind.
Spoon pecan mixture on top of Brie. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Spread on crackers.

title: graham cracker deluxe
directions: Place graham crackers on 3 aluminum foil sheets.
Mix together butter, brown sugar, pecans and vanilla.
Bring to a boil. Dribble over crackers, getting some of each cracker.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Watch carefully.
Cool and break apart.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and toss well to combine.
Serve with corn chips.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, Crisco and baking powder.
Take out 1 cup for top.
Mix milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry mixture and mix. Makes 2 cakes in 9-inch pans.

title: french coconut pie *
directions: Blend together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Mix in milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until delicately brown.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Wash and hull berries.
Crush 1 cup and cook with water for 2 minutes; sieve.
Blend sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in berry juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until glaze is thick and clear. Stir in food coloring.
Spread a small amount of glaze on bottom of shell.
Arrange half of berries in pastry shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Repeat.
Chill 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: fat-free muffins
directions: Mix together oatmeal, bran, baking powder, cinnamon and sweetener with a fork.
Add
to
this
mixture the egg whites, milk and vegetable oil
which
has	been
mixed together.
Mix until moist.
Add remaining ingredients and mix with a fork or spoon.
Spoon into muffin	pan
which
has
been
lined
with Baker's paper cup liners.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Store in tightly covered container
in
freezer or refrigerator.
No cholesterol, no fat and
low
in calories!	Yields 12 muffins. Doesn't rise.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Chill jello until slightly stiff; add cream cheese and beat well.
Add whipped cream and remaining ingredients; mix well and allow to chill.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Place yolks in bowl and mash.
Add mayonnaise and relish, and mix well. Fill egg halves with yolk mixture.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: Let raspberry sherbet soften.
Add chocolate chips and stir. Form into an oblong, rounded form on a cookie sheet (kind of like 1/2 football).
Freeze until firm (about 2 hours).
Soften pineapple sherbet and spread over the shape about 1/2-inch thick. Freeze until firm.
Soften lime sherbet.
Hold out 1/4 of the lime sherbet for the final step.
Spread 3/4 of lime sherbet over the shape and freeze until firm.
The remaining sherbet will be mixed lightly with green food coloring (should be dark green and light green together).
Spread final mixture carefully.
Do not blend. Should be streaked with dark and light.
Freeze.
Cut into slices like you would watermelon and serve.
Can be cut ahead of time, wrapped in plastic wrap (each slice) and frozen until ready to serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first three ingredients, and mix well.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls, and then roll into 3 tbsp. sugar and 3 tbsp. cinnamon combined.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart at 400 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: quick beef-vegetable soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in next 10 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 30 minutes. Prepare Creamettes spaghetti according to package instructions. Drain.
Add to soup mixture.
Heat through.
Serve with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Refrigerate or freeze leftovers.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: jumbo sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in big mixing bowl.
Batter will be runny.
Put about 6 cookies or 1/3 cup batter for each cookie on cookie sheet. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for approximately 6 minutes.

title: rice pilaf with peas
directions: In twelve-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp.
With slotted spoon, remove bacon to paper towels; set aside.

title: french bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat with a spoon until thoroughly mixed.
Gradually add remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Knead on a lightly floured surface for 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is elastic and not sticky.
Place in a greased bowl; cover dough with plastic wrap.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size, 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Punch down.

title: toasted butter pecans(microwave)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole or pie plate, place pecan halves. Sprinkle seasoned salt.
Cut margarine in 4 pieces and arrange evenly over top of pecans.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes. After 3 minutes in the microwave, I stir the pecans so they are all coated with the butter and sprinkle a few shakes of seasoned salt.
They will burn easily.

title: chicken tortellini alfredo
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package, adding broccoli to water during last 3 minutes of pasta cooking time; drain.
Heat sauce and chicken breast strips in saucepan on medium heat 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Toss all ingredients.
Makes 3 servings.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Dissolve soda and applesauce.
Add to shortening mixture.
Sift salt, cinnamon and cloves with part of the flour.
Add to shortening mixture.
Add enough of the flour to make a fairly stiff batter.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: classic chocolate fondue
directions: Break chocolate into triangular pieces.
Combine all ingredients in small chafing dish or fondue pot.
Stir over direct low heat until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
For dunking, use apple slices, banana chunks, seedless grapes, pineapple chunks (fresh or frozen), strawberries, tangerine sections, angel food or sponge cake, etc.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, mix slightly thawed potatoes with all other ingredients, except corn flakes.
Treat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with oil.
Put mixture in pan and sprinkle corn flakes over evenly-spread mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook, debone and chop chicken. Add chopped celery, pickles and eggs. Stir in mayonnaise, salt, pepper and seasoning salt to taste.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 350° until set.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Combine margarine and Crisco with sugar.
Gradually add milk and vanilla.
Beat at high speed with electric mixer for 10 to 20 minutes, until very creamy and frosting is not grainy (from sugar).
Frosts 1 cake (2 layers or 9 x 13-inch pan).

title: mushroom-clam salad
directions: Clean mushrooms with brush, trim and slice.
Core, rinse and shred lettuce; chill.
Mix clam juice with oil, vinegar, salt, tarragon, dill weed and Tabasco sauce.
Toss with mushrooms and onion.
Chill until ready to serve, or toss immediately with lettuce.
Garnish top with tomatoes and avocado.

title: phyllo spinach squares
directions: Arrange 6 sheets of the phyllo in the bottom of a 15 x 10-inch baking pan; brush with margarine between each sheet.
(Allow edges of dough to overlap.)
Spread souffle over dough.
Sprinkle with water chestnuts.
Top with remaining phyllo; brush with margarine again between each sheet.
Fold edges of phyllo toward center; brush with remaining margarine.
Score top layers into 48 squares or diamonds.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Cut through all layers.
Makes 48.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with salt and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in cubes and stir in all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole or pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut sides off bread and cut into three strips.
Cut each piece of bacon into three pieces.
Spread cream cheese onto each strip of bread.
Roll up tight, wrap a piece of bacon around each roll and stick with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put in blender in order listed.
Start on low, turn on high for 5 seconds.
Place on well-greased griddle.
Brown on both sides.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fairy delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° or 325° in a glass pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine crumbs and butter and press into 2 baking dishes.

title: marinated tomatoes(servings: 4)
directions: Place tomato slices in serving bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Chill for 1 hour or longer before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well with a hand beater on medium speed.
Pour filling into pie shells and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in layers in baking dish.
Between each layer put cheese and onions.
Cover with soup.
Top with layer of crushed Cheez-Its and sliced margarine.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, then eat.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: Drain water from water chestnuts; wrap 1 slice of bacon around 1 chestnut.
Secure with rounded toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet. Continue until bacon is finished.
Bake in 425° oven.

title: cobblestone candy
directions: Melt the first 5 ingredients together.
When cool, add the colored miniature marshmallows.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut when hardened.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Finely chop the onion; crush the garlic.
Put with rest of ingredients except for the oil into a bowl and mix well together. Shape mixture into walnut-sized balls.
Fry the meatballs in shallow oil for about 15 minutes, turning once.
Arrange on a warmed serving plate and serve with rice, pasta or gravy.

title: peg's meringue(for pie)
directions: Moisten cornstarch with a little bit of cold water.
Stir in boiling water with sugar added.
Cook until clear.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually add cooked cooled mixture to egg whites.
Beat until mixture stands in stiff peaks. Spread over pie and brown in 350° oven.

title: old fashion meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Press firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes; drain.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl. Stir in cornmeal.
Beat eggs slightly in a separate bowl.
Pour the beaten eggs, milk and melted butter in the dry ingredients. Stir until well mixed.
Spoon a heaping teaspoonful of batter onto wax paper.
Coat dumplings with a little extra cornmeal.
Drop dumplings into simmering stock or stew.
Cover tightly for 15 minutes.
Do not remove cover.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Return to pot.
Add salt, sour cream and onion.
Mix. Mix together the oleo and stuffing mix. Place 1/2 in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour and spread the soup mixture over the top; do not stir.
Put remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cook until brown.
Serves 8.

title: speedy chile con carne(crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
(I brown mine by placing in a heatproof dish and season with garlic salt and pepper. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir well to break up the beef. Microwave an additional 2 to 3 minutes.

Pour into colander which has been placed over a large bowl and allow to drain completely.) Combine in the crock-pot the browned beef, chile brick (I use Owens, as in sausage packaged just like the sausage but it is chile.
If not available, any chile brick, usually found in refrigerated case at grocery), water, canned beans and tomato sauce.
Stir well and allow to heat on low for 4 to 6 hours. I use this chile for enchiladas, taco salad, chile with rice or just plain old chile!

title: poor boy supper
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add beans and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove skin and fat from chicken.
Put into pot with water, celery, onion, salt and thyme. Simmer until chicken is tender. Refrigerate and let chicken mixture cool.
Lift out chicken pieces and remove bones.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Measure 3 1/2 to 4 cups of broth; strain broth and add flour mixed with a small amount of cold water.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from stove and cool.

title: pickled hot dogs
directions: Cut up hot dogs and onion and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pour sauce over hot dog chunks and onion slices.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate several days before serving.

title: stacey's sunshine eggs
directions: We were living on base at Williams AF Base at the time our youngest daughter was in junior high school.
She learned to make these in school and for weeks we would have them every Sunday morning.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss first three items in a large bowl.
Mix together 3 spices.
Add to mixture.
Serve chilled.

title: low-fat pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust according to package, except do not add cooking oil.
Instead, spray dough with cooking spray.
Prepare crust in pizza pan sprayed with cooking spray.
First, spread sauce, then add cheese, then add remaining toppings.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Place pizza on lowest oven rack and cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: hoppin' john
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Fry and drain well, reserving 6 tablespoons of bacon grease.
Rinse and drain black-eyed peas. Mix all ingredients in skillet with reserved bacon drippings. Heat thoroughly and serve with cornbread, if desired.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix all together, adding nuts and vanilla at the end. Pour into a greased square pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, then add last three ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: donna's quick skillet supper
directions: Brown meat and add Worcestershire sauce. Add Veg-All, tomato sauce and salt to meat. Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Drop potatoes around sides of skillet. Top with cheese. Sprinkle paprika on top. Heat in oven until cheese is melted.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix with 1/4 cup flour.
Mix with fork.

title: yummy chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Stir well.
Beat in eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in chips, pecans and coconut.
Mixture will be thick.
Pour in unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cover pie shell edges if they brown too quickly.
I use semi-sweet mini chips.
Other chips may be substituted.

title: quick and easy tomato sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, brown garlic in olive oil.
Pour can of sauce over it.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer gently for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned taffy
directions: Mix sugar, water and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Cook, without stirring, until it begins to turn yellow.
Pour onto marble slab or large cookie sheet and add flavoring and food coloring, if desired.
As soon as it whitens, then stretch out and cut into bars.
Wrap individually.

title: cream puff squares
directions: Bring to a boil the water and oleo; add flour.
Let cool. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Soak dates in boiling water with 1 teaspoon soda.
Let cool!! Mix together shortening, sugar, date and water mixture, nuts, egg and vanilla.
Sift remaining dry ingredients into wet ones.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).
Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Pour over cake mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to directions.
Add condensed milk and 1/3 carton of Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mixture.
Repeat.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top.
Place wafers around edge.
This fills a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill in refrigerator until you're ready to serve.

title: andrea's split pea soup
directions: Wash and drain split peas.
Combine peas, ham hocks, fresh vegetables and seasonings in a Dutch oven.
Cover with about 2 1/2 quarts water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove ham hocks; take meat off of bones.
Dice ham and add to peas.
Slice sausage, adding to soup.
Add frozen peas; simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crusty, warm French bread.
Serves 10.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Blend softened butter and grated cheeses.
Add garlic powder. Using a rolling pin, roll each slice thin.
Spread on mixture, not too thick.
Roll up into logs.
Set in tray.
Cover with foil; freeze.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° 15 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks from whites.
In small mixer bowl, combine yolks and remaining ingredients, except olives.
Beat until smooth. Spoon or pipe into egg halves.
Garnish with olives.
Refrigerate. Yield:
24 halves.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Combine mashed carrots with rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Spread topping over carrots and return to oven for about 25 minutes.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate in Good Seasons Italian dressing. (Make according to directions on packet.)

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: In pan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Cook until candy melts.
Set aside.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, melted margarine, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Mix until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough into pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle chips.
Spread with melted caramel mix.
Crumble second half of dough over all.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in bars.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix eggs, spinach, Ricotta cheese and spices together.
Spray bottom of 9-inch square baking dish with Pam.
Place 1 layer of lasagna noodles and spread with 1/2 of spinach mix.
Pour a thin layer of sauce to cover.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses and some Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 6 to 8 minutes. Place butter and cream in skillet over medium-low heat.
Stir constantly until blended and mixture bubbles for 2 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in Parmesan cheese until thoroughly blended and fairly smooth.
Pour sauce over noodles and serve immediately.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in margarine until tender. Cook broccoli according to directions on box; drain well.
Combine all ingredients and heat.
Heat until cheese is melted (cut cheese in pieces to melt faster).

title: spaghetti sauce
