directions: Place ground meat and margarine in a 4-quart pot and brown meat. Add chopped onion and simmer until clear.
Add canned ingredients and stir until smooth. Stir in water, Italian seasoning, oregano, garlic powder and black pepper.
Cover and cook over low flame, stirring occasionally. Simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti and top with Parmesan cheese.
Also can be frozen for easy quick lunches and meals.

title: cherry-apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch square baking dish. Combine cherry pie filling and apples in pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon and Raisin Bran.
Add butter.
Mix well. Add melted butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle flour mixture over fruit. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serves 6.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, chili powder, cottage cheese and 1/3 bottle of taco sauce.
Put in a pie carrier.
Brown hamburger.
Add the rest of the taco sauce in the hamburger.
Put on top of the dip.
Put shredded lettuce, onion, black olives, tomato and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat
eggs
and
sugar well and add milk.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon
or vanilla flavoring (I use both), then coconut. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: almond cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Spray spring-form pan, 9 x 3-inches, with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle bottom with almonds.
Beat egg whites in medium bowl until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Beat remaining ingredients in large bowl until fluffy; fold into egg whites.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn off oven; leave cheesecake in oven 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours but no longer than 48 hours.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles, then drain and add bouillon cube.
Brown garlic, onion and beef in oil.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream. Cook on low until heated through.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place onion and bell peppers on top.
Mix tomato sauce, water and mustard.
Pour over chops and chill for 1 hour.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix together and pour into 10 x 12-inch glass casserole dish. Season to taste.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until softened.
Add rest of ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling point.
Add Jell-O until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and beat with a hand beater.
Mix well.
Add water and mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in all other ingredients and chill.
Serves 6 to 8 when prepared in 8-inch square pan.
For 9 x 13-inch, double the recipe.

title: dippin chili pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread over a pizza pan bottom.
Top with can of chili and sprinkle with the cheese.
Put under broiler to melt cheese (just a few minutes).
Just dip in with chips!

title: dressing for fruit salad
directions: Melt oleo; stir in flour.
Do not brown it.
Blend pineapple juice and when it starts to thicken, add marshmallows.
Stir until blended and melted.
Be sure not to let the mixture boil. Let cool and place in refrigerator.
Pour generously over fruit salad.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Flatten down on ungreased pan. Makes 4 dozen.

title: haupia (coconut pudding)*
directions: *For prepared coconut milk, pour 2 cups boiling water over 4 cups grated coconut and let stand 20 minutes.
Strain mixture through double thickness of cheese cloth, pressing to remove all liquid.
Capture the liquid.
Yields about 2 cups prepared coconut milk.

title: deer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Mix again, then divide into 6 rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil, press bottom and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Age 1 week.

title: barley soup
directions: Add mushrooms if your family likes them.
Soak 1/4 cup dried mushrooms in warm water for 30 minutes.
Save the water.
Put the barley into boiling water and let simmer.
Saute onion in oil; add drained chopped mushrooms and brown slightly.
Add to barley.
Add carrots, celery, cabbage and potatoes to oil in frying pan and saute until limp.
Sprinkle flour over and fry cabbage until it gets brown around the edges.
Strain reserved mushroom water and add.
Bring to a boil and let it boil for 1 minute.
Add to the barley.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until barley is done.
Serve in warm soup bowls.

title: hot creamy beef dip
directions: Beat cheese with sour cream until light.
Stir in beef, onion, pepper and garlic salt.
Turn into a shallow baking dish (can be prepared up to this point in advance).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or favorite dunking chips.

title: watergate salad
directions: Make pudding using juice from pineapple for liquid.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well and chill.

title: cheese roll
directions: Grate all cheese and chop up cream cheese (I use a big roast pan).
Add remainder of ingredients.
Let cheese warm to room temperature.
Mix well.
Roll into logs and then roll in chili powder.
Makes about 8
6-inch logs.
Wrap each in Saran Wrap, then in foil and refrigerate.
Slice and serve with crackers.

title: cheese spinach appetizers
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs with flour until smooth.
Squeeze spinach to dry, then add to egg mixture along with cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, pepper, cayenne and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with wheat germ and bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, then cut into 1 1/2 inch squares. Yield:
48 squares.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 3 g, fat 2 g, calories 32.

title: jello dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix dry Jell-O, cottage cheese, drained pineapple and whipped topping in large bowl all together.

title: frances wright's angel flake yeast biscuits
directions: Add the dissolved yeast to the buttermilk, sugar and salt. Sift together the flour, soda and baking powder.
Cut in the butter.
Mix all together; do not knead.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.
Pinch off amount needed.
Knead, roll and cut into biscuits; don't let raise.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned and cooked through.
Can be refrigerated 4 to 5 days.

title: lazy woman's meatballs
directions: Mix together in a large crock-pot.
Heat on high until hot, about 2 hours.
Great with barbecue sauce too.
I use the Italian-style meatballs from Rosina.

title: coconut pie cake
directions: Combine, mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked pineapple
directions: In baking dish, put 1/2 of the pineapple and 1/2 of the Ritz crackers.
Dot with margarine.
Repeat the layers.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pecan pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: halloween cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on 32 crackers and cover with another cracker, sandwich style.
Melt chocolate chips separately in a double boiler with 1 tablespoon shortening per bag.
(This also can be accomplished in a microwave oven on very low heat, stirring at 1-minute intervals.)
Dip the peanut butter crackers in the chocolate to cover evenly.
Set aside on waxed paper.
When chocolate is firm, decorate with icings and gumdrops.

title: cheesy spinach pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Separate dough into 4 rectangles; press perforations to seal. Spread rectangles with cheese to within 1/4-inch of edges. Top with ham and spinach. Starting at shortest side, roll up each rectangle. Press edges to seal. Cut each roll into 6 slices. Place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 24 appetizers.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt chips and margarine on low heat.
Cool.
Add eggs by blending into chocolate mix.
Add marshmallows and 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: onion pie
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Cover bottom of your dish with some crackers.
Layer onions, soup and crackers.
Repeat until dish is full.
Mix egg with enough milk to cover layers and pour over all.
Cook at 350° until set, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked yams with orange sauce
directions: Wash yams and wrap in boil.
Bake until tender, cool and peel. In a greased (butter or margarine) casserole, slice yams approximately 1/2-inch thick.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling into a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over cherries.
Put cake mix on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Top with pats of butter (from the stick of butter). Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sugar-free pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with Lite Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Combine egg, pumpkin, sugar and pie spice in a medium bowl. Spread over bottom of pie shell.

title: lazy wife pie
directions: Melt margarine in long cake pan or large iron skillet.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk; pour in pan on top of margarine. Have your fruit hot; place drained fruit on top of crust mixture. Bake at 375° until done.
I usually use 2 to 3 cups fruit. Reserve juice of fruit to pour over pie when served, if desired. Any fruit will work.

title: white chili
directions: Cut chicken in 1/2-inch chunks and saute in oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and onion and stir until chicken is lightly browned.
Add salsa, beans, cooking sauce and cilantro.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and additional cilantro if desired.

title: roasted red pepper spread
directions: Drain and rinse roasted red peppers.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Put remaining six (6) ingredients in blender and whirl until capers and parsley are finely chopped.
Add peppers.
Pulse with on/off motion until peppers are coarsely chopped.
Serve with crackers or Italian bread.

title: pan cream puffs(just like sander's hot fudge cream puffs)
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring butter and water to a boil.
Add flour and remove from heat.
Mix together until the dough forms a ball.
Place dough in a mixing bowl and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Spread this mixture on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown (it will puff up, don't worry.)
Let cool.

title: simple bouillabaisse
directions: In
a
large 14-inch Dutch oven simmer onions in butter until slightly browned.
Add peppers, potatoes, clams, garlic, bay leaf, parsley
and
salt.
Cook for a few minutes longer. Add
boiling water.
Cover
and gently simmer for 25 minutes. Add the fish fillets and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and scallops	and cook
for
more minutes.
Add tomatoes, clam juice and
blend. Add
the
crab
meat and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Blend milk and pudding mix.
Add pumpkin, spice and Cool Whip. Pour into prepared pie crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Garnish top with spoons of Cool Whip and pecan halves.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding, milk, sour cream and Cool Whip until thick.
Put half of this mixture on top of crackers.
Place another layer of crackers, then put remainder of filling.
Top with crackers, then chocolate frosting. Chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 30 seconds.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Pour in pie shell.
Mix whipping cream and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Cover pie and refrigerate.
Garnish with toasted coconut.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: If you want to make meringue separate eggs. I don't, so I beat eggs, flour, then add milk, then sugar and vanilla.
Half and half makes this pie richer and tastier.
Bake at 350° until it is set good.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; cut a slice off stem end.
Scoop out center and mash; strain and save liquid.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon into tomato cups.
Pour 1 tablespoon tomato liquid over each tomato.
Place in close fitting baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup hot water to dish.
Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve hot.

title: turkey tetpa
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook together for a few minutes.
Use with any type meat such as beef.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bar in double boiler.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add beaten egg yolk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Spread mixture evenly on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake!
While still warm, spread melted chocolate over cookie mixture and sprinkle chopped nuts evenly over top.
Cut in squares while still warm (important!).

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and all other ingredients, except nuts. Shape into balls; roll in nuts.

title: peanut butter layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt, completely covering pan.
Then put crushed graham crackers in pan.
Next mix condensed milk and peanut butter together.
Pour over graham crackers.
Then sprinkle granola over that.
Next, pour chocolate chips over it, then coconut on top of all this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown (varies with oven). Make sure it's completely cool before removing from pan.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Mix the other ingredients.
Place potatoes in a buttered baking dish and pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: liver patties
directions: In food processor, grind liver, onions and egg.
Stir in salt, pepper, milk and bread crumbs.
Make into patties and fry.

title: ham-potatoes au gratin
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese and mayonnaise until cheese melts.
Put potatoes and ham with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Add to cream mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add milk and water with yeast; mix well.
Dump on floured board; cut out.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven.
The dough will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: picadillo(pee-ka-dee-yo)
directions: In 10-inch skillet with cover, saute onions, green pepper, garlic and beef in margarine or oil (stirring to break up meat) until meat is browned.
Sprinkle with salt, black pepper and oregano.
Add olives, cooking sherry, raisins and small green peas. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Last 5 minutes, garnish with sliced tomatoes.
Serve on rice.

title: broiled eggplant
directions: Make crisscross cuts in inside surface.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix a crushed clove of garlic with about 1/4 cup olive oil; brush over eggplant.
Sprinkle lightly with mixture of fine dry bread crumbs and grated Parmesan cheese.
Drizzle with a little more oil.
Place in greased broiler pan and broil, very, very slowly until golden on top and eggplant is tender.
Takes 10 to 20 minutes depending on thickness of vegetable.
No need to turn eggplant.

title: adams apple
directions: Put filling in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Slightly beat egg and add vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add egg to flour mixture. Mix until crumbly.
Spread on apples.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Put raisins in a pan and cover with water; let come to a boil. Set aside and drain off water.
Beat eggs well, then mix with other ingredients, except pecans.
Put into unbaked pie crust and sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake until done.

title: vanilla nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan. Mix sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts. Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked rice
directions: Butter
9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Saving some cheese for top, mix all together.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°, then uncovered
for 35 to 45 more minutes.
Top with cheese 10 minutes before it's done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy pecan pudding cake
directions: Make sauce by combining first 3 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add chopped nuts. Spread batter into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Carefully pour sauce over batter.
Arrange pecan halves on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower(microwave)
directions: Cook head
of
cauliflower
minutes on 100% on High. Add the remaining ingredients and cook on 70% for 2 minutes or slow cook 3 to 4 minutes.

title: bug balls
directions: Mix above ingredients and add small amount of water to form soft dough.
Make into small balls and place in corners of cabinets, drawers, and closets to eliminate bugs.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook broccoli and any other vegetables you want to use.
Arrange on bottom of cooking pan; put chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix together soup, milk, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder and pour over vegetables and chicken. Put cheese on top of soup mixture.
Melt oleo and mix with corn flake crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
(You can use other vegetables, but cut down on chicken and have vegetables cover bottom of pan.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together using only as much flour to handle.
Too much flour will make them hard.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
You can put some sugar on top or a raisin.

title: pour crust peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in an 8 x 12-inch oblong baking dish. Pour peaches into baking dish.
Use peach juice also.
Combine other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour this mixture evenly over the sliced peaches.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops in flour, cornmeal mixture.
Melt butter in cake pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Brown meat on one side and turn.
Mix onion and barbecue sauce; pour over chops and cook in a slow oven until tender.
Cover pan with foil before baking.

title: lasagna la scala
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain; rinse well.
Cut steaks into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Brown well in oil in a large 12-inch skillet.
Add mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water, garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and basil. Boil gently, uncovered, for 20 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and pour into a baking dish.
Cut 3 slices of bacon into bite sized pieces and put on top of beans.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: aunt louise's chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Combine dry ingredients and add to bowl.
Mix cocoa with hot or boiling water until thick and add to batter.
Mix well.
Pour into Turk's head baking pan.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Test with toothpick to be sure cake is done.
Let cake cool in pan; then remove from pan and ice cake.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place all ingredients except apples and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Beat with wooden spoon until blended.
Add apples and nuts and blend together. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool; sprinkle with sugar.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pour remaining crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift the powdered sugar with 2 cups flour and salt.
Cut in the cup of butter with a pastry blender.
Pat down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Whip sour cream about 3 minutes.
Drain juice off oranges and pineapple and add whipped cream.
Also add coconut and marshmallows and add all together to whipped cream.
Candied cherries can also be added, if desired.

title: hopping john
directions: Empty the peas into a colander. Rinse thoroughly in cold water while removing pebbles and defective peas.
Place the ham hocks in a pot containing about 3-inches of cold water.
Cover the pot and place it over a very high flame.
Once the water begins to boil, add the rinsed black-eyed peas.
Lower flame. Season to taste with the salt, bay leaf, cayenne pepper, black pepper, garlic powder and Cajun spice.
Replace lid.
Stir periodically. Add small amounts of water as needed.
Cook until done.

title: creamy broccoli, rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Cook rice beforehand (1 cup dry rice).

Heat oven to 350°. Combine undiluted soup, sour cream, horseradish cream, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, parsley and 1 cup of cheese. Layer rice, broccoli, mushrooms and soup mixture into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until heated through and broccoli is tender.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cover and refrigerate.
The longer it sets, better it tastes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High until melted (1 to 2 minutes).
Stir in parsley, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Cover.
Microwave at High until shrimp are pink, opaque and tender (do not overcook or shrimp will be tough), 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes, stirring twice. Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.
Serves 4.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine and stir in greased 2-quart dish.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours at 325°.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add tomato sauce; simmer together for 2 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions until tender; drain.
While piping hot, mix in cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
In an 11 3/4 x 9 3/8 x 1 1/2-inch aluminum pan, put one layer of noodle mixture, then one of meat mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with a layer of noodles on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Freeze.
To bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and bake for 30 minutes.

title: grandma gordon's olive and nut spread
directions: In a medium bowl combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and olive juice together until creamy.
Add chopped olives and walnuts; mix well.
Chill for 1 hour and serve with stone wheat crackers.

title: seaside salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Serve when cold.

title: light french toast
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk, sugar and liquid sweetener.
Mix well.
Dip bread in mixture.
Cook over stove in skillet sprayed with nonstick spray at medium-high heat until done on both sides. Serve with lo-cal syrup.

title: pineapple macadamia cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, using hands or the back of a spoon, mix Macadamia nuts and graham cracker crumbs. Add sugar and butter and combine well.
Press mixture into bottom and three-quarters of the way up the sides of a ten-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: mary jo's potato soup
directions: Mix water and bouillon cube, then add next 6 ingredients. After tender, add milk and flour, mixed together before you add to mixture.
When all begins to thicken, add cheese.

title: hobo pack
directions: Divide meat into patties, put on foil.
Slice potatoes on meat, then carrots and onions.
Salt, wrap foil around package and bake in 400° oven until done, about 1 hour; or put all in one pan and cover with foil and bake.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoon in 10x sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet 9 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese rum fudge
directions: In mixing bowl combine cream cheese and milk, gradually adding sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, rum flavoring and chocolate.
Add 1 cup of nuts.
Pour fudge into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, buttered.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Chill.
For variety, substitute rum flavoring with orange or almond.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine rest in a saucepan.
Bring to rolling boil.
Then pour over mixture in bowl and stir thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Ready when cool.
Fancy up with chopped nuts, candied fruit, raisins or any combo.

title: sausage and broccoli noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine Ragu Cheese Creations sauce and milk.
Stir in sausage, broccoli, noodles, 3/4 cup cheese and roasted peppers.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, evenly spread mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: turkey and sausage jambalaya
directions: In 1/2 stick margarine, cook turkey and sausage until done. Set aside.
In large stock pot cook in 2 sticks margarine and saute vegetables until clear.
Add tomatoes, Tabasco sauce, seasonings and chicken stock.
Bring to boil.
Add rice and bring back to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer over low heat 15 minutes or until most of liquid is gone.
Serve with your favorite cornbread and collard greens.

title: venison dried beef
directions: Mix ingredients.
Do not add water.
Divide meat into three equal parts.
Rub mixture on each piece of meat for three days. Put in a jar or crock.
(Will make its own brine.)
Leave for one week to 10 days, depending on size of pieces.
Rinse off salt brine and hang to cure.

title: pasta shells florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, egg white, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg until blended.
Fill each shell with a heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture.

title: mae's fruit cake
directions: Cut pineapple and cherries into large chunks.
Put into large mixing bowl with pecans and dates.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and mix into fruit.
Beat eggs with flavorings and pour over.
Stir until smooth.
Add melted candy, mixing well (use hands).
Put mixture into baking pans lined with foil.
Bake for two hours at 250°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon.
Sprinkle sugar on top, then add mayonnaise.
Spread evenly, then add cheese. Cover; refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
Toss just before serving.

title: western dressing mix
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Store in airtight container until ready to use.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Season and brown chops.
Arrange chops in baking dish or large frying pan with onion and rice and cover with tomatoes and juice. Cover tightly and simmer over low heat or bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: striped delight
directions: Prepare pudding using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread 1 1/2 cups thawed Cool Whip over pudding.
Garnish.
Optional: Layer with pecans and bananas.
Makes 15 servings.

title: tater skins
directions: Slice potatoes thin; place on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bacon bits. Bake for 20 minutes at 400° in preheated oven. Serve hot!

title: mud pie
directions: Use a pie plate and crush Oreo cookies to cover the bottom, 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Open Oreo cookies and line the sides of the pie pan.
Make pudding according to box directions; pour over the cookies.
Refrigerate until pudding cools.
Frost with the Cool Whip and use 2 Oreo cookies, crushed fine to sprinkle over the Cool Whip.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Bring to a boil water, margarine and cocoa.
Add to flour mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Bake cake mix per instructions on box.
When done and still hot, punch holes in top with a fork.
Mix milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Let it completely cool and spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with all of a small can of coconut.

title: no bake cheese pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into large graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Top with fruit (optional).

title: old french canadian pea soup
directions: Prepare all vegetables.
Place in stock pot, add meat and broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and add water as needed to keep liquid about 2/3 full.
Simmer on low heat for 3-4 hours until done.
Bon Appetit!

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Place butter in saucepan along with marshmallows, stir until completely dissolved.
Add raisins, pecans, cherries and graham crackers; mix well.
(Your hands work wonderfully.)
Add cherry juice and vanilla and complete mixing.
Place all ingredients in a Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Garnish with pecans, cherries and raisins.
Refrigerate until ready to serve, approximately 2 hours.
Cake will keep up to 6 months in foil or tin.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in 1/4-cup water and sprinkle over dates in a small bowl. Let stand while creaming margarine and sugar together. Add eggs. Beat well. Stir in date mixture. Add salt and flour. Blend well. Stir in nuts and coconut. Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Do not overcook. Don't stack; place wax paper between layers of cookies.

title: easy fudge
directions: Place chocolate in microwave safe bowl and microwave on high for 2 or 3 minutes. Stir often or chocolate will burn. Add vanilla, pecans, milk and salt. Let cool slightly, then add marshmallows. Put into a greased 8-inch square pan, let it cool completely, then cut into squares. Enjoy.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Roll eggs in flour.
Cut sausage into 8 equal parts.
Spread sausage around egg.
Chill.
Dip sausage egg in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs with paprika mixed in.
Place on a shallow pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until sausage is cooked. Cut eggs into eighths and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Place chicken and salt in a Dutch oven; cover with water. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Set aside 1/4 cup broth; reserve remaining broth for other uses.
Bone chicken and chop; set aside.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oats and
buttermilk together.
Add egg yolks and beat good. Add dry ingredients
and oil.
Last, add stiffly beaten whites.
Fry on hot griddle and serve with meaty gravy of your choice.

title: sugarless cookies for diabetics
directions: Boil raisins and prunes or dates in water for 3 minutes, then cool.
Add vegetable shortening; cool completely.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients; mix well together.
Chill cookie dough for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Place broccoli spears in dish.
Layer chicken chunks on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice and spread over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: When cheese is softened to room temperature, grate or mash until creamy.
Pour pimento with liquid from jar and mash with fork until fine.
Combine cheese and pimento.
Add 1/2 cup mayonnaise; salt and pepper to taste.
Cream or mix until fluffy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Blend in small mixer until the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle topping over the casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This can be made ahead of time and frozen before baked.
Thaw and bake as instructed when ready to use.

title: mom's punch
directions: Chill liquids.
Combine with frozen concentrates; mix well. Pour into punch bowl and add carbonated water just before serving. Makes about 22 (4 ounce) servings.

title: turtles or caramels
directions: Rinse pan with cold water.
Cook and stir syrup, sugar and butter until boiling.
Slowly add canned milk or light cream. Cook and stir occasionally until it begins to change color.
Stir constantly until mixture reaches firm ball stage.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: easy potato rolls
directions: Cream shortening, gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add salt, potatoes and eggs and beat until smooth.
Dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water.
Stir; add to potato mixture along with other 2/3 cup warm potato water.
Stir to make a soft dough, knead and place in well-oiled bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls or loaves; let rise again until doubled.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with butter.
Yields about 45 rolls.

title: chili con queso
directions: Steam onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in top of double boiler until soft, 20 to 30 minutes. Add Velveeta and American cheese. Mix well.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Butter a 12 x 16-inch shallow pan.
Mix together all ingredients and press into pan.
Prick dough and slightly cut into 2-inch squares.
Bake at 270° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut when still hot.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Fill 1 large stewing pot with hot water; set on medium-high. Dice the onion, carrots and celery very small and add to the water.
Add your beef bouillon cubes, salt and pepper and let simmer.
Cook hamburger in separate pan, then add to the soup. Let soup simmer until veggies are tender, then serve with rolls.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and pineapple chunks in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt. Repeat layers.
Top with pineapple slices.
Cover with pineapple juice.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake until top is brown.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sun glow salad
directions: Bring water and sugar just to a boil.
Dissolve jello in the hot mixture.
Put in refrigerator and let chill until it gets syrupy.
Beat the Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add the pineapple and cheese Fold in jello mixture.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: mounds
directions: Heat and melt butter.
Stir in milk and confectioners sugar. Mix in coconut and make into small balls.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving to blend flavors.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add sweet potatoes; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, spices and vanilla; mix with sweet potatoes, eggs, sugar and butter.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light. Add dry ingredients (flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt), then blend in molasses; mix well. Form dough in small balls, rolling them in your hands. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until top rounds or cracks. Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Press excess moisture from broccoli. Combine cornbread mix, eggs, chopped onion, cheese, butter and seasonings; stir well. Stir in broccoli. Spoon mixture into a greased 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in one cup sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and ginger.
Fold into pumpkin.
Spread mixture in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: turnip au gratin
directions: Bring about 1/2-inch water to boil in a pan.
Add turnips, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cover; cook until tender.
Drain; remove and set aside.
In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine. Blend in flour, pepper and remaining salt.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove and gradually stir in milk.
Return to heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Mix cheese sauce and turnips together.
Put into baking dish. Melt remaining margarine; add bread crumbs. Sprinkle over turnips. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crumbs are toasted.

title: banana pineapple dream
directions: Beat 1 stick butter (margarine) for 10 minutes (important step).
Add eggs, confectioners sugar and vanilla; continue to beat.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Blend Crisco and butter.
Add sugar.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add alternately flour and Seven-Up to mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Mix in mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, egg and onion. Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Boil lasagna noodles.
Simmer browned hamburger with sauce for 30 minutes.
Layer in 2-quart dish.
Put hamburger sauce first, noodles, then cheese.
Repeat until top of dish is filled.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream in butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In bowl beat egg, milk and salt.
Add macaroni, mix well.
Spread evenly in greased 10 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Combine Ro-Tel with spaghetti sauce and spoon over macaroni mixture.
Top evenly with other ingredients, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: trish's cookies
directions: Put flour in large bowl. Make a hole in the flour and pour other ingredients. With hands, mix thoroughly, working flour in a little at a time with the other ingredients. Roll dough on floured board. Cut with cookie cutter and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until golden.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, just until broccoli separates with a fork.
Drain most of the water off and return to burner.
Reduce heat and add undiluted soup.
Stir until mixture is fully blended.
Mix in cheese and simmer for a few minutes.
Put in glass casserole and cook in microwave for 5 minutes with lid on and for 5 minutes with lid off.
(This can be baked in conventional oven at 350° for 30 minutes instead of microwave.) Sprinkle with French fried onions if preferred.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables with 1 teaspoon salt, garlic salt and 2 tablespoons butter in 1/2 cup water for 15 minutes.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Place vegetables in buttered casserole.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Stir in flour to make smooth paste.
Add reserved vegetable liquid and sour cream to make 2 cups liquid.
Cook slowly until thick.
Add remaining salt, Cheddar cheese, nutmeg and thyme.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix crumbs with remaining butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Slice Velveeta and melt in microwave.
Mix taco mix and Ro-Tel tomatoes with melted cheese. Add meat to cheese mixture.

title: tuna salad
directions: Dissolve jello gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Blend in cold water, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Chill until very thick. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart bowl.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp salad greens.
Serve with additional mayonnaise.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Saute bacon, onion, celery and garlic in medium pot.
Mash peas in liquid and add, along with asparagus, bacon, potato or turnip and ham.
Add a pinch of pepper, pinch of parsley and a pinch of thyme.
Remove from heat.
Add half and half.

title: ada's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and soda.
Mix together sour cream and extracts. Add to dry ingredients.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook beef and green pepper; drain. Cook macaroni; drain. Combine all except cheese, and put in baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese mixture and bake at 325 degrees until cheese melts.

title: polish sausage supreme
directions: Slice sausages into coin shapes or smaller.
Cook in large skillet with onion, green pepper and margarine until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes which have been chopped fine or blended slightly with salt, ground pepper and rice.
Cook on medium or low heat until rice is done, adding water when needed.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 6 pieces lengthwise.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle sugars and cinnamon over potatoes.
Pour melted oleo over.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Serves 6.

title: chop meat soup
directions: Fry chop meat and onion in pot and drain fat.
Put in all ingredients and cook on a low flame for about 1 to 2 hours.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Put everything together in a big pot; cook until vegetables are soft.
Serve with shredded cheese on top.

title: covered dish dinner
directions: Crumble beef into a large bowl. Stir in soup mix, soup, onion, rice and water and mix well. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer or until the cheese is melted. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: croissants
directions: Cut rolls into halves.
Mix cream cheese and chives.
Put into the center of rolls.
Roll up like a diaper and wrap with bacon. Line pan with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion soup.
Add shrimp and mix well. Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: mother's buttermilk-pineapple ice
directions: Mix first three items together.
Pour into ice cube pans and start to freeze until frozen just around edges of pan.
Remove from freezer and add last two items.
Return to ice cube pans and put in freezer until completely frozen.
Good summer treat.

title: clam digger spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add oil and garlic.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Combine flour with juice from a can of clams; blend until smooth.
Stir into butter mixture.
Add clams and remaining clam juice, parsley, Tabasco, thyme and rosemary. Simmer sauce about 10 minutes.
Turn hot spaghetti into serving dish.
Add clam sauce and toss gently.
Sprinkle with pimento. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oil pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Pour oil and milk in measuring cup.
Do not stir.
Add all at once to flour, stirring with a fork until a ball is formed.
Divide.
Roll each
half between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Remove top paper and turn pastry into pie pan. Remove other pastry and fit pastry to pan.
Cut even with rim. Add filling.
Roll out top crust as you did the bottom crust.
Place over filling and fold edges under bottom crust.
Seal with a fork. Slit near center for steam to escape.
Makes two 9-inch crusts.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix broth and stuffing together.
Mix soup and milk together. Line baking dish with chicken, pour soup mixture over top, then moistened dressing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once.
Pour into hot, well-oiled skillet or pan or make 12 muffins.
Bake at 450° for approximately 20 minutes.
Time may vary according to your oven. Serve hot and stand back and wait for hugs and kisses from your family.
They will love it.

title: sunday baked ham
directions: Trim fat and rind from ham.
Score outside of ham in a diamond pattern and stud with cloves.
Place ham on a rack coated with cooking spray and place rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Combine sugar and next 3 ingredients in a small saucepan; stir well. Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool. Brush over ham.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and continue baking 1 hour, basting ham with sugar mixture every 15 minutes.
Yields 23 servings.
